{"type":"message","id":"90f28027","parentId":"fe2cd287","timestamp":"2026-03-08T12:48:56.454Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking why I can't run openclaw commands. Let me explain clearly.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Fair question. Two reasons:\n\n**1. I'm sandboxed.**\nMy `exec` tool runs inside a Docker container — isolated from the host system. The `openclaw` CLI is installed on your VPS host, not inside my container. So when I try to run `openclaw`, it's just not there.\n\n**2. Even if it were, agent deployment changes system config.**\nThat falls into the \"ask before acting\" category. Spinning up 5 new persistent agents is a significant system change — not something I should do silently in the background.\n\n---\n\n**What you can do right now:**\n\nSSH into your VPS and run:\n```bash\nopenclaw agent --help\n```\n\nPaste the output here and I'll give you the exact commands to deploy all 5 agents. Should take about 5 minutes once we know the syntax."}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":230,"cacheRead":23481,"cacheWrite":395,"totalTokens":24109,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.00345,"cacheRead":0.0070443,"cacheWrite":0.0014812500000000001,"total":0.01198455}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772974130695}}
