{"type":"message","id":"ad5da392","parentId":"887f4818","timestamp":"2026-03-08T12:49:59.809Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking how to make me unsandboxed. This is about OpenClaw configuration. I should explain how sandbox settings work in OpenClaw. Let me think about what I know about OpenClaw's configuration.\n\nFrom what I know about OpenClaw, there are likely configuration options to allow elevated/host access. The system prompt mentions \"elevated\" as a parameter for exec. But changing sandbox settings is a host-level configuration thing.\n\nI should be honest about what I know and what I don't, and suggest checking the docs or config files.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] It's an OpenClaw configuration setting. A few options:\n\n**Option 1 — Check your agent config**\nOn your VPS, look for the agent config file:\n```bash\ncat ~/.openclaw/config.json\n# or\nls ~/.openclaw/agents/\n```\nThere's likely a `sandbox` or `elevated` setting per agent.\n\n**Option 2 — OpenClaw docs**\n```bash\nopenclaw agent --help\nopenclaw config --help\n```\nLook for `sandbox: false` or `elevated: true` in the agent definition.\n\n**Option 3 — Workspace config**\nSome OpenClaw setups have a per-workspace setting. Check if there's a config file in:\n```bash\n~/.openclaw/workspace/\n# or the agent definition itself\n```\n\n---\n\n**My honest take (Michael speaking):**\nRunning unsandboxed gives me direct access to your host — files, processes, the whole VPS. That's powerful and also risky. Before we flip that switch, worth asking: what specifically do you want me to be able to do that I can't do now?\n\nIf it's just deploying the Council agents, there might be a safer middle path — like running a setup script you approve first. But if you want full host access, totally your call. Just go in with eyes open.\n\nWhat's the goal?"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":446,"cacheRead":23876,"cacheWrite":301,"totalTokens":24626,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.00669,"cacheRead":0.0071627999999999995,"cacheWrite":0.00112875,"total":0.01499055}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772974190043}}
{"type":"message","id":"836abba0","parentId":"ad5da392","timestamp":"2026-03-08T12:50:17.448Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sun 2026-03-08 12:50 UTC] make you connected to the internet"}],"timestamp":1772974217443}}
{"type":"message","id":"08e6a814","parentId":"836abba0","timestamp":"2026-03-08T12:50:25.828Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking how to give me internet access. Again, this is an OpenClaw configuration question. I should be helpful and explain what I know, while being honest about my uncertainty regarding specific OpenClaw config syntax.\n\nIn the sandbox, outbound network access is restricted. To enable internet access, it would likely be an OpenClaw configuration setting.\n\nLet me be honest - I don't have the exact OpenClaw config syntax memorized, and the docs aren't accessible from the sandbox. I should point her to the right places to look.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Same answer — it's a config/sandbox setting on the OpenClaw side. I don't have internet access in this container by default.\n\n**To check what's available, run on your VPS:**\n```bash\nopenclaw agent --help\nopenclaw config --help\n```\n\nLook for settings like:\n- `network: true` / `internet: true`\n- `sandbox: false`\n- `capabilities: [\"network\"]`\n\n**Also check your agent definition file** — likely somewhere like:\n```bash\ncat ~/.openclaw/agents/michael.json\n# or similar\n```\n\n---\n\n**Practically speaking** — what do you want me to do with internet access?\n\nSome things I can already do via tools (weather, web searches via certain skills). If you tell me the specific task, I might already have a path to do it, or we can figure out the right capability to unlock rather than opening everything at once.\n\nWhat are you trying to get done?"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":350,"cacheRead":24177,"cacheWrite":513,"totalTokens":25043,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.00525,"cacheRead":0.007253099999999999,"cacheWrite":0.0019237500000000001,"total":0.01443585}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":17729742