{"type":"message","id":"78124ae1","parentId":"3b761a83","timestamp":"2026-03-08T12:58:51.261Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. The model in use is `amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6`. The user wants `claude-sonnet-3-5` but that model isn't available (only Sonnet 4.6 is configured). I should use the available model or check if Sonnet 3.5 can be added.\n\nAlso - sandbox is already `mode: \"off\"` with `workspaceAccess: \"rw\"` - that's why I have access now.\n\nFor deploying agents, I need to:\n1. Create workspace directories for each agent\n2. Set up SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, AGENTS.md in each workspace\n\n\n3. Run `openclaw agents add` for each\n\nI'll set up workspaces for Rafael, Uriel, Gabriel, and Raguel with their own configuration files, then deploy them using the available Sonnet 4.6 model since the requested 3.5 version isn't accessible.\n\nFor each agent, I need to create a workspace containing their SOUL.md (which directly embeds their character), along with IDENTITY.md, USER.md (pointing to Lucy as principal), and AGENTS.md for behavioral guidelines.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Good. Only one model is configured (`amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6` — Sonnet 4.6, not 3.5). I'll deploy with the available model and flag that. Now building all 4 agent workspaces and deploying:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_PwuihrdwfKmo56bVHWlxUb","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"for agent in rafael uriel gabriel raguel; do\n  mkdir -p ~/.openclaw/workspace-$agent\n  echo \"Created workspace-$agent\"\ndone"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":645,"cacheRead":34005,"cacheWrite":635,"totalTokens":35286,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.009675,"cacheRead":0.010201499999999999,"cacheWrite":0.00238125,"total":0.02226075}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772974720926}}
