{"type":"message","id":"a549f1e7","parentId":"ff0ca046","timestamp":"2026-03-08T13:30:27.066Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `openclaw` user was added to the `docker` group during OpenClaw's setup. Here's why:\n\n**OpenClaw uses Docker for sandboxing.** When sandbox mode is `on`, agent code runs inside isolated Docker containers. The `openclaw` user needs Docker access to spin those containers up and tear them down.\n\nSince you turned sandbox mode **off**, Docker isn't being actively used right now — but the group membership stays.\n\n**Why this matters (Michael flagging):**\nBeing in the `docker` group is effectively equivalent to root access, even without sudo. Docker can mount the host filesystem, run privileged containers, etc. With sudo now also enabled, you've given me full unrestricted access to this VPS.\n\nThat's fine if this is a dedicated DataFloat machine — just worth knowing explicitly. If other things are running on this VPS, it's worth a conversation about what I should and shouldn't touch.\n\n**Is this a dedicated VPS for the Council, or is other stuff running on it?**"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":226,"cacheRead":43858,"cacheWrite":229,"totalTokens":44314,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.0033900000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0131574,"cacheWrite":0.00085875,"total":0.017409149999999998}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772976620498}}
