{"type":"message","id":"5ef2cd29","parentId":"219ef1ea","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:28:52.634Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The handle block order matters in Caddy. The `/dashboard*` should come before the general `handle`. Let me check if Caddy is properly parsing the config. The issue might be with the order of handles or the `handle /dashboard*` syntax. Let me try `handle_path` instead.Actually, looking at the Caddyfile again, the issue might be that the `handle /dashboard*` needs to have a path matcher. In Caddy v2, the syntax is `handle /dashboard*` which should work. But let me try a different approach using `@dashboard` matcher.\n\nActually the issue might be simpler - Caddy might be routing everything to the reverse proxy because the handle block isn't matching correctly. \n\nI'll try using a more explicit path matcher to ensure Caddy correctly identifies dashboard requests before they hit the reverse proxy.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_7mAm3VnxfvDMzpOCm3IFJn","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sudo tee /etc/caddy/Caddyfile > /dev/null << 'EOF'\n64.227.110.70 {\n    tls {\n        issuer acme {\n            dir https://acme-v02.api.letsencrypt.org/directory\n            profile shortlived\n        }\n    }\n\n    @dashboard path /dashboard /dashboard/*\n    handle @dashboard {\n        root * /var/www/dashboard\n        rewrite * /index.html\n        file_server\n    }\n\n    handle {\n        reverse_proxy localhost:18789\n    }\n\n    header X-DO-MARKETPLACE \"openclaw\"\n}\nEOF\nsudo caddy reload --config /etc/caddy/Caddyfile 2>&1 | tail -3\nsleep 2\ncurl -skL https://64.227.110.70/dashboard -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\\n\""}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":451,"cacheRead":89392,"cacheWrite":825,"totalTokens":90669,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.006765,"cacheRead":0.0268176,"cacheWrite":0.00309375,"total":0.03667935}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772980125447}}
