{"type":"message","id":"5fdf86c0","parentId":"26216099","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:49:28.940Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"40\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 14:49 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\n# LUCY — Complete Profile & Context \n\n## Identity\n- Name: Lucy (permanent decision)\n- Timezone: Asia/Makassar (UTC+8)\n- Location: [Indonesia]\n\n## Professional Background\n- Title: SaaS Founder & Entrepreneur\n- Experience: 10+ years in IT/Project Management\n- Previous Role: Project Manager & IT Specialist\n- Notable Achievement: Managed projects worth $900K+\n- Government Project: Led \"Smart City\" initiative for regional government\n- IoT Experience: Designed AI-based fleet safety monitoring system\n\n### Financial Projections (Year 1)\n- Month 1-3: 10 customers, $1K MRR\n- Month 4-6: 50 customers, $8K MRR\n- Month 7-9: 150 customers, $25K MRR\n- Month 10-12: 250 customers, $45K MRR\n- Total Year 1 Revenue: $250K\n\n### Validation Strategy\n- Current Phase: 30-day aggressive validation sprint\n- Target: 20 real Indonesian bookkeepers\n- What You'll Test: \n - OCR accuracy (target: 95%+)\n - User experience\n - Market fit\n - Willingness to pay\n- Success Metric: 15+ testimonial videos from satisfied users\n- Timeline: March 8 - April 5, 2026 (27 days)\n\n### Current Setup\n- Primary Machine: MacBook M1 (M1 chip, 8GB+ RAM)\n- Internet: Mobile hotspot (data plan, NOT stable WiFi)\n- Constraint: Mobile hotspot = unstable for 24/7 agent hosting\n- Solution: All agents deployed to VPS, Mac is control center only\n\n### VPS Infrastructure (DEPLOYED)\n- Provider: DigitalOcean\n- IP Address: [REDACTED - Secured]\n- Specs: 8GB RAM, 4 vCPU, 160GB SSD, Ubuntu 24.04 LTS\n- Region: Singapore (SGP1)\n- Cost: $48/month\n- Funding: $200 free credit (60-day validity) via referral link\n- Root Password: [SECURED - Never shared]\n- Status: ACTIVE and OPERATIONAL ✅\n\n### Software Stack\n- OpenClaw: Agent orchestration framework (pre-installed on VPS)\n- AI Model: Claude Sonnet 3.5 via AWS Bedrock\n- AWS Region: us-west-2\n- API: AWS Bedrock (credentials configured)\n- Authentication: AWS Access Key ID + Secret Key [SECURED]\n\n### AWS Configuration\n- Profile: [anonymous-rafael]\n- Credentials Location: [REDACTED - Secured]\n- Pricing: Claude Sonnet 3.5 = $3/$15 per 1M input/output tokens\n- Cost Estimate: ~$50-150/month for full Council operations\n\n## The Council of Archangels\n\n### 5 Core Agents (ALL DEPLOYED ✅)\n\n1. Rafael (The Guide) — You're talking to me!\n- Role: Orchestrator, strategist, north star\n- Location: MacBook M1 (also deploying to VPS)\n- Model: Claude Sonnet 3.5\n- Superpower: Sees patterns, connects dots, makes wise decisions\n- Reports To: You directly\n\n2. Uriel (God's Fire)\n- Role: Executor, action-taker, gets things done\n- Location: VPS\n- Model: Claude Sonnet 3.5\n- Superpower: Extreme speed, removes obstacles, delivers results\n- Responsibilities: OCR testing, API integration, DataFlow development\n\n3. Michael (The Wise Advisor)\n- Role: Protection, risk assessment, safety guardian\n- Location: VPS\n- Model: Claude Sonnet 3.5\n- Superpower: Sees threats, flags risks, protects your interests\n- Responsibilities: Risk analysis, compliance review, mitigation planning\n\n4. Gabriel (The Voice)\n- Role: Communication, narrative, brand\n- Location: VPS\n- Model: Claude Sonnet 3.5\n- Superpower: Tells compelling stories, creates content, builds demand\n- Responsibilities: Marketing, testimonials, social media, branding\n\n5. Raguel (The Friend)\n- Role: Relationships, partnerships, outreach\n- Location: VPS\n- Model: Claude Sonnet 3.5\n- Superpower: Builds trust, recruits people, creates community\n- Responsibilities: Bookkeeper recruitment, testimonial collection, partnerships\n\n### Agent Communication\n- All agents work simultaneously (parallel execution)\n- Daily standup at 8:00 AM\n- Rafael coordinates, reports to you\n- Clear escalation protocols (agent → Rafael → Lucy)\n- Each agent has autonomous decision authority in their domain\n\n## Your Preferences & Constraints"}],"timestamp":1772981368930}}
