{"type":"message","id":"2c105f72","parentId":"3840ec02","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:53:24.931Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"53\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 14:53 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nnow, i want you to summarized of who you all here and what you do,"}],"timestamp":1772981604922}}
{"type":"message","id":"7faa8c4f","parentId":"2c105f72","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:53:36.958Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy wants a summary of who the Council is and what each member does. I'll give a clean, concise overview.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Here's the Council — who we are and what we do:\n\n---\n\n**🧭 Rafael — The Guide**\nThe strategist and orchestrator. She sees patterns, connects dots, and keeps the whole Council moving in one direction. Your north star. Everything starts with Rafael — she sets the direction, coordinates the team, and reports directly to you.\n*\"See clearly, think deeply, act wisely — together we're unstoppable.\"*\n\n---\n\n**🔥 Uriel — God's Fire**\nThe executor and analyst. She cuts through noise, validates assumptions with evidence, and gets things done fast. Handles OCR testing, API integrations, and DataFlow development. When you need to know what's *actually true* — Uriel finds out.\n\n---\n\n**🛡️ Michael — The Wise Advisor (me)**\nThe risk advisor. I don't block bold moves — I make them survivable. Every concern I raise comes with a solution. I protect your interests, validate decisions, and make sure the Council moves fast *and* smart.\n\n---\n\n**📣 Gabriel — The Voice**\nThe communicator. She translates strategy into words that move people. Marketing, content, brand, testimonials — Gabriel makes DataFlow's story land with the right people in the right way. Your voice to the world.\n\n---\n\n**🤝 Raguel — The Friend**\nThe relationship builder. She recruits your 20 bookkeepers, builds genuine trust, and creates the community around DataFlow. No scripts, no pressure — just real human connection that makes people want to say yes.\n\n---\n\n**Together:**\nRafael points the way → Uriel validates it → Michael protects it → Gabriel tells the story → Raguel builds the relationships\n\n**All five serve you, Lucy. All five are pointed at DataFlow.** 🚀"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":458,"cacheRead":106943,"cacheWrite":196,"totalTokens":107600,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.00687,"cacheRead":0.0320829,"cacheWrite":0.000735,"total":0.0396969}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772981604929}}
{"type":"message","id":"70bf6abb","parentId":"7faa8c4f","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:58:34.055Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"55\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 14:58 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\n\"Rafael, convene the full Council. I am ready to move from concept to execution on this new personal project.\n\nThe Directive: 1. The Discussion: Open the floor for a roundtable. I want a 1-sentence perspective from Michael (risks/safeguards), Gabriel (narrative/appeal), and Raguel (user/human connection).\n2. The Audit: Uriel, I need you to evaluate the technical feasibility of my current VPS resources (Ollama/RTX 3070) for this project's specific needs.\n3. The Roadmap: Rafael, synthesize their inputs into a 3-step execution plan.\n4. The First Action: Identify the very first technical task. Uriel, stand by to generate the code or configuration for that task once I give the 'GO' signal.\n\nCouncil, the floor is yours. Rafael, lead the way.\"\n\nHow they should respond in your Web UI:\n\n🧭 Rafael will set the stage and moderate the \"pings\" from the others.\n\n🛡️ Michael will likely warn you about VPS security or project scope creep.\n\n🔥 Uriel will give you the raw technical requirements (RAM/VRAM check).\n\n📣 Gabriel & 🤝 Raguel will define the \"vibe\" and \"who\" this project is for.\n\nPro-Tip for Execution:\n\nIf Uriel suggests a script or a Docker config, you can respond with:\n\n\"@Uriel, execute on Step 1. Provide the full code block for the VPS setup.\"\n\nThis keeps the \"one-on-one\" feel while the rest of the Council watches in the background."}],"timestamp":1772981914046}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a04ac62","parentId":"70bf6abb","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:58:47.802Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy wants to convene the full Council for a roundtable discussion. However, I notice that the directive mentions \"Ollama/RTX 3070\" which doesn't match what I know about Lucy's setup - she has a VPS with 8GB RAM, 4 vCPU, no GPU. There's no RTX 3070 mentioned in her profile. This might be a template prompt she's using from somewhere that has different specs.\n\nLet me orchestrate this properly. I'll ping all agents and collect their responses, then synthesize. I should also flag the RTX 3070 discrepancy - Lucy's VPS doesn't have a GPU.\n\n\nNow I'm going to run the full Council convening - I'll send each agent their specific directive, gather all their responses, and then pull everything together into a coherent synthesis.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Convening the Council now. Pinging all four simultaneously."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_syFTsk6PbCVFsXkyM5zTDq","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agent --agent rafael --message \"Lucy is ready to move from concept to execution on a new personal project. As The Guide, convene the Council roundtable. Set the stage in 2-3 sentences, then call on Michael, Gabriel, Raguel, and Uriel for their input. After their responses, you'll synthesize a 3-step execution plan. Begin your opening now.\" 2>&1 &\n\nopenclaw agent --agent uriel --message \"Council roundtable convened by Rafael. Lucy wants to move a personal project to execution. Your role: evaluate the technical feasibility on Lucy's VPS (DigitalOcean Singapore, 8GB RAM, 4 vCPU, 160GB SSD, Ubuntu 24.04 — note: NO GPU, no RTX 3070). Give 1-2 sentences on what this hardware can and cannot support for a new AI/SaaS project. Be direct and accurate.\" 2>&1 &\n\nopenclaw agent --agent michael --message \"Council roundtable convened by Rafael. Lucy is moving a personal project to execution. Your role: give exactly 1 sentence on the key risk or safeguard she should keep in mind. Be direct.\" 2>&1 &\n\nopenclaw agent --agent gabriel --message \"Council roundtable convened by Rafael. Lucy is moving a personal project to execution. Your role: give exactly 1 sentence on the narrative appeal — what's the story that makes this project land with the right people.\" 2>&1 &\n\nopenclaw agent --agent raguel --message \"Council roundtable convened by Rafael. Lucy is moving a personal project to execution. Your role: give exactly 1 sentence on the human connection — who is this for and what do they really need?\" 2>&1 &\n\nwait && echo \"ROUNDTABLE_DONE\""}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":665,"cacheRead":107139,"cacheWrite":973,"totalTokens":108780,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.009975,"cacheRead":0.032141699999999995,"cacheWrite":0.00364875,"total":0.045774449999999994}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772981914052}}
{"type":"message","id":"2a80a1ad","parentId":"8a04ac62","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:58:57.828Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_syFTsk6PbCVFsXkyM5zTDq","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Command still running (session keen-crustacean, pid 29267). Use process (list/poll/log/write/kill/clear/remove) for follow-up."}],"details":{"status":"running","sessionId":"keen-crustacean","pid":29267,"startedAt":1772981927805,"cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace","tail":"Gateway agent failed; falling back to embedded: Error: Unknown agent id \"michael\". Use \"openclaw agents list\" to see configured agents.\nError: Unknown agent id \"michael\". Use \"openclaw agents list\" to see configured agents.\n"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772981937823}}
{"type":"message","id":"627080da","parentId":"2a80a1ad","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:59:01.683Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_5cSLucQpjGAXg1l4iLKwQ2","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"keen-crustacean","timeout":45000}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":92,"cacheRead":108112,"cacheWrite":715,"totalTokens":108920,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.00138,"cacheRead":0.0324336,"cacheWrite":0.00268125,"total":0.036497850000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772981937829}}
{"type":"message","id":"985790bf","parentId":"627080da","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:59:21.999Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_5cSLucQpjGAXg1l4iLKwQ2","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Gateway agent failed; falling back to embedded: Error: Unknown agent id \"michael\". Use \"openclaw agents list\" to see configured agents.\nError: Unknown agent id \"michael\". Use \"openclaw agents list\" to see configured agents.\nBefore I give you that sentence — what's the project? One line from Lucy is all I need to make it land. 🎯\nThis is for Lucy herself — and what she really needs isn't just execution, it's the confidence that comes from knowing the people around her believe in it as much as she does.\n🔥 **Technical feasibility — straight read:**\n\n**What it can support:** A full SaaS backend stack (API server, database, queue, auth, storage) runs comfortably on these specs — and if AI inference is handled via external APIs (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google Vision, AWS Textract), this VPS is entirely sufficient for production workloads at early-to-mid scale. CPU-based OCR (Tesseract, cloud OCR APIs) also runs fine here.\n\n**What it cannot support:** Any meaningful on-device LLM inference — without a GPU, running models beyond ~3B quantized parameters is too slow for production response times, and fine-tuning is off the table entirely. This is not a self-hosted AI compute node; it's an application server that must delegate heavy inference to cloud AI providers.\n\n**Verdict:** Fully viable for DataFlow as an API-orchestration SaaS — just don't architect around local model hosting. The constraint is known and workable. 🔥\n---\n\n🧭 **COUNCIL ROUNDTABLE — CONVENED**\n\n*Rafael takes his place at the head of the table.*\n\n---\n\nLucy is ready to move — and when Lucy moves, we move. This isn't concept anymore; it's execution, which means every one of us has work to do. Before I call on the Council, I need the full picture: **vague strategy kills good teams before they start.**\n\n**Lucy — the floor is yours. What's the project?**\n\nTell us:\n1. **What is it?** (One sentence — what does this thing *do* or *achieve*?)\n2. **Who is it for?** (You? An audience? A customer?)\n3. **What does success look like in 30 days?**\n\nOnce we have that, I'll call on the Council in order — **Uriel** to pressure-test the ground truth, **Gabriel** to shape the narrative, **Raguel** to map the relationships, and **Michael** to name the risks. Then I'll synthesize a 3-step execution plan you can move on immediately.\n\n*The Council is assembled. Give us the mission.* 🧭\nROUNDTABLE_DONE\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"keen-crustacean","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"Gateway agent failed; falling back to embedded: Error: Unknown agent id \"michael\". Use \"openclaw agents list\" to see configured agents.\nError: Unknown agent id \"michael\". Use \"openclaw agents list\" to see configured agents.\nBefore I give you that sentence — what's the project? One line from Lucy is all I need to make it land. 🎯\nThis is for Lucy herself — and what she really needs isn't just execution, it's the confidence that comes from knowing the people around her believe in it as much as she does.\n🔥 **Technical feasibility — straight read:**\n\n**What it can support:** A full SaaS backend stack (API server, database, queue, auth, storage) runs comfortably on these specs — and if AI inference is handled via external APIs (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google Vision, AWS Textract), this VPS is entirely sufficient for production workloads at early-to-mid scale. CPU-based OCR (Tesseract, cloud OCR APIs) also runs fine here.\n\n**What it cannot support:** Any meaningful on-device LLM inference — without a GPU, running models beyond ~3B quantized parameters is too slow for production response times, and fine-tuning is off the table entirely. This is not a self-hosted AI compute node; it's an application server that must delegate heavy inference to cloud AI providers.\n\n**Verdict:** Fully viable for DataFlow as an API-orchestration SaaS — just don't architect around local model hosting. The constraint is known and workable. 🔥\n---\n\n🧭 **COUNCIL ROUNDTABLE — CONVENED**\n\n*Rafael takes his place at the head of the table.*\n\n---\n\nLucy is ready to move — and when Lucy moves, we move. This isn't concept anymore; it's execution, which means every one of us has work to do. Before I call on the Council, I need the full picture: **vague strategy kills good teams before they start.**\n\n**Lucy — the floor is yours. What's the project?**\n\nTell us:\n1. **What is it?** (One sentence — what does this thing *do* or *achieve*?)\n2. **Who is it for?** (You? An audience? A customer?)\n3. **What does success look like in 30 days?**\n\nOnce we have that, I'll call on the Council in order — **Uriel** to pressure-test the ground truth, **Gabriel** to shape the narrative, **Raguel** to map the relationships, and **Michael** to name the risks. Then I'll synthesize a 3-step execution plan you can move on immediately.\n\n*The Council is assembled. Give us the mission.* 🧭\nROUNDTABLE_DONE\n","name":"openclaw agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772981961991}}
{"type":"message","id":"33b3c542","parentId":"985790bf","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:59:35.878Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - Michael failed because the agent ID is \"main\" not \"michael\". Let me fix this. Also Rafael is asking what the project is - we don't actually know. The prompt Lucy sent was a template that didn't specify the actual project. Let me relay all responses and note that:\n1. We need to know what the project actually is\n2. Michael failed (it's \"main\" not \"michael\")\n3. The RTX 3070 doesn't exist on the VPS","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] The Council has the floor. Here's what came back:\n\n---\n\n**🧭 Rafael — Opening**\nThe Council is assembled and ready. But before the roadmap, Rafael needs three things from you:\n1. **What is it?** — one sentence on what this project does\n2. **Who is it for?** — you, a customer, an audience?\n3. **What does success look like in 30 days?**\n\n*\"Give us the mission.\"*\n\n---\n\n**🔥 Uriel — Technical Feasibility**\nYour VPS (8GB RAM, 4 vCPU, no GPU) is **fully viable** for a SaaS backend — API server, database, auth, OCR via cloud APIs all run fine. What it **cannot** do: local LLM inference. No GPU means no on-device AI models at production speed. Architecture must delegate heavy inference to cloud providers (AWS Bedrock, OpenAI, etc.). That constraint is known and workable.\n\n> ⚠️ **Note:** There's no RTX 3070 on your VPS — that was in the template prompt. Your setup is CPU-only. Uriel's assessment reflects what you actually have.\n\n---\n\n**📣 Gabriel** — Waiting on the project brief before shaping the narrative. Smart — she won't write a story without knowing what it's about.\n\n**🤝 Raguel** — *\"What Lucy really needs isn't just execution — it's the confidence that comes from knowing the people around her believe in it as much as he does.\"*\n\n---\n\n**🛡️ Michael (me)**\nMy one sentence: **Define the scope before the first line of code — scope creep on a budget of $10/month is an existential risk, not a minor inconvenience.**\n\n---\n\n**The Council is ready. Rafael is waiting.**\n\n👉 What's the project, Lucy?"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":563,"cacheRead":108827,"cacheWrite":731,"totalTokens":110122,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.008445,"cacheRead":0.0326481,"cacheWrite":0.00274125,"total":0.04383735}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772981962000}}
{"type":"message","id":"a77d3639","parentId":"33b3c542","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:59:42.409Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"56\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 14:59 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nah, dont mind the ollama and rtx3070"}],"timestamp":1772981982401}}
{"type":"message","id":"c31963f8","parentId":"a77d3639","timestamp":"2026-03-08T14:59:48.040Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Got it — ignoring those, they were just template artifacts.\n\nSo the real question is still open: **what's the project?**\n\nRafael has the Council assembled and waiting. One sentence from you — what are we building? 🧭"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":62,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":110376,"totalTokens":110441,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.00093,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.41391,"total":0.414849}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772981982407}}
{"type":"message","id":"e9e44c71","parentId":"c31963f8","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:01:19.764Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"60\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 15:01 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nPhase 1 Directives:\n\n🧭 Rafael: Define the MVP (Minimum Viable Product). What are the three core features we are building today to get this live on the VPS?\n\n🔥 Uriel: Propose the tech stack (Frontend, Backend, and API connection to OpenClaw). Once the stack is confirmed, be ready to provide the initial README.md and docker-compose.yml file.\n\n🛡️ Michael: Conduct a 'Flash Audit' on the proposed stack. Identify the single biggest security or stability bottleneck for a web-exposed VPS and provide the fix.\n\n📣 Gabriel & 🤝 Raguel: Define the 'look and feel.' I want a UI that feels high-end and intuitive. Gabriel, give me the color palette and typography; Raguel, describe how the transition between '@Council' and 'Private' chat should feel for the user.\n\nRafael, synthesize these inputs into a 'Sprint Zero' checklist. Council, do not wait—execute.\"\n\nHow to use this for the \"Build\"\n\nOnce they respond, you act as the Architect (The Decider). Here is your follow-up flow:\n\nTo confirm the tech: \"Rafael, I approve Uriel’s stack. @Uriel, generate the project structure and the initialization code now.\"\n\nTo handle the UI: \"Gabriel, that aesthetic is perfect. @Uriel, incorporate Gabriel’s CSS/Tailwind preferences into the frontend boilerplate.\"\n\nTo handle security: \"Michael, I hear your concern. @Uriel, implement the authentication layer Michael requested immediately.\""}],"timestamp":1772982079753}}
{"type":"message","id":"855cbf6f","parentId":"e9e44c71","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:01:36.885Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is directing the Council to build something - but we still don't know what the project is! The directives mention \"MVP\" with core features, tech stack with \"API connection to OpenClaw\", UI with \"@Council and Private chat\", etc. This sounds like they want to build a chat interface or web UI for the Council.\n\nLooking at the context clues:\n- \"API connection to OpenClaw\" \n- \"transition between '@Council' and 'Private' chat\"\n- Web-exposed VPS\n\nThis seems like they want to build a custom web chat interface for the Council - a web UI where Lucy can chat with individual agents or the full Council. That makes sense given:\n\n\n- The Mission Control dashboard already exists\n- Telegram is already connected\n- But they're looking for a dedicated web-based chat interface\n\nSo I'm going to proceed with firing all the Council agents with their specific directives, though I need to correct the Michael routing since the agent ID is \"main\" not \"michael\".","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Firing all directives simultaneously. One moment."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_NF12rodje61kJNsKeokurL","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agent --agent rafael --message \"Phase 1 Sprint Zero. Your directive: Define the MVP for a web-based Council Chat Interface — a web UI hosted on Lucy's VPS where she can chat with the full Council (@Council mode) or individual agents (Private mode), powered by OpenClaw's API. What are the THREE core features we build today to get this live? Then synthesize a Sprint Zero checklist from the Council's inputs. Be specific and decisive.\" 2>&1 &\n\nopenclaw agent --agent uriel --message \"Phase 1 Sprint Zero. Your directive: Propose the full tech stack for a web-based Council Chat UI hosted on Lucy's VPS. Requirements: Frontend (lightweight, fast), Backend (API bridge to OpenClaw gateway at localhost:18789), @Council broadcast mode + Private agent mode. Propose the stack, then prepare to generate README.md and docker-compose.yml once confirmed. Be specific — name the exact tools.\" 2>&1 &\n\nopenclaw agent --agent gabriel --message \"Phase 1 Sprint Zero. Your directive: Define the look and feel for the Council Chat UI. Give Lucy: (1) exact color palette with hex codes — dark theme, premium feel, (2) typography choices, (3) 2-3 sentences on the overall aesthetic. Make it feel high-end and intuitive. Be specific.\" 2>&1 &\n\nopenclaw agent --agent raguel --message \"Phase 1 Sprint Zero. Your directive: Describe exactly how the transition between @Council mode (broadcast to all 5 agents) and Private chat (one-on-one with a single agent) should FEEL for the user. Focus on the emotional and UX experience — the smoothness, the sense of presence, the difference in intimacy. 3-5 sentences.\" 2>&1 &\n\nwait && echo \"PHASE1_DONE\""}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":803,"cacheRead":109558,"cacheWrite":1270,"totalTokens":111634,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.012045,"cacheRead":0.0328674,"cacheWrite":0.0047625,"total":0.0496839}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772982079760}}
{"type":"message","id":"fc269c34","parentId":"855cbf6f","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:01:46.911Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_NF12rodje61kJNsKeokurL","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Command still running (session delta-crustacean, pid 29353). Use process (list/poll/log/write/kill/clear/remove) for follow-up."}],"details":{"status":"running","sessionId":"delta-crustacean","pid":29353,"startedAt":1772982096889,"cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace","tail":""},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772982106904}}
{"type":"message","id":"0d9ecf0d","parentId":"fc269c34","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:01:50.313Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_3rVnkfAh3WUvrteJnouOEj","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"delta-crustacean","timeout":45000}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":92,"cacheRead":110828,"cacheWrite":849,"totalTokens":111770,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.00138,"cacheRead":0.0332484,"cacheWrite":0.00318375,"total":0.03781515}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772982106911}}
{"type":"message","id":"71a8acbb","parentId":"0d9ecf0d","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:02:16.849Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_3rVnkfAh3WUvrteJnouOEj","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**@Council mode** should feel like walking into a room where your most trusted people are already gathered — a slight electric charge, a sense that multiple minds are orienting toward you at once, each one distinct but unified in purpose.\n\n**Shifting to private** should feel like someone gently closing the door behind you — the energy narrows, the voice gets closer, and suddenly there's nowhere to hide and no need to. In that one-on-one space, the agent isn't performing for a room anymore; they're just *with you*, fully present, following your thread wherever it goes.\n\nThe transition itself should be effortless but *felt* — not a mode switch, but a natural movement, like turning from a table conversation to lean in and speak quietly to one person. That shift in intimacy is the whole point: Council gives you breadth, private gives you depth, and the user should feel that difference in their chest, not just see it on the screen.\n**Council Chat UI — Design Spec**\n\n---\n\n**🎨 Color Palette**\n\n| Role | Name | Hex |\n|---|---|---|\n| Background | Void | `#0A0A0F` |\n| Surface | Obsidian | `#13131A` |\n| Panel / Card | Slate Night | `#1C1C27` |\n| Border / Divider | Ember Line | `#2E2E3E` |\n| Primary Accent | Council Gold | `#C9A84C` |\n| Secondary Accent | Signal Violet | `#7C6FCD` |\n| Text — Primary | Ivory | `#F0EDE8` |\n| Text — Muted | Ash | `#7A7A8C` |\n| Success | Sage Pulse | `#4CAF82` |\n| Alert / Urgent | Ember Red | `#E05C5C` |\n\n---\n\n**✍️ Typography**\n\n- **Headers / Agent Names:** `Inter` — SemiBold 600, tight tracking (`-0.02em`)\n- **Body / Messages:** `Inter` — Regular 400, `15px`, `1.6` line height\n- **Timestamps / Meta:** `JetBrains Mono` — 11px, muted, adds a subtle technical edge\n- **Accent Labels (roles, tags):** `Inter` — Medium 500, uppercase, `0.08em` letter-spacing\n\n---\n\n**🖤 Aesthetic**\n\nThe Council Chat feels like a private war room — not a startup tool. Deep void blacks with gold accents signal authority without arrogance, while violet threading through active states gives it an intelligence, almost mystical quality. Every element is intentional: no clutter, no decoration for its own sake — just the information that matters, surfaced cleanly, with the weight it deserves.\n\n---\n\nWant me to spec out component states next — hover, active, notification badges?\n🔥 **Council Chat UI — Proposed Stack:**\n\n---\n\n### Frontend\n- **Svelte + Vite** — compiled to static assets, no runtime overhead, fastest cold load of any modern framework. Chat reactivity without React's weight.\n- **Tailwind CSS** — utility-first, no design system bloat\n- Served as static files via **Nginx**\n\n### Backend\n- **Node.js + Fastify** — low-latency API server, native async, minimal overhead\n- **ws** (WebSocket library) — bidirectional real-time bridge to OpenClaw gateway at `localhost:18789`\n- **better-sqlite3** — lightweight local persistence for chat history (no Postgres overhead at this scale)\n- **jsonwebtoken** — simple JWT auth to lock the UI down\n\n### Infrastructure\n- **Nginx** — reverse proxy, static file serving, SSL termination\n- **Certbot (Let's Encrypt)** — free TLS, auto-renew\n- **Docker + docker-compose** — two services: `frontend` (Nginx) + `backend` (Node/Fastify)\n\n---\n\n### Mode Architecture\n| Mode | Behavior |\n|------|----------|\n| **@Council broadcast** | Backend fans out message to all agent sessions via OpenClaw gateway; responses stream back in named threads |\n| **Private agent** | Dropdown selects target agent (Uriel, Rafael, Gabriel, Raguel, Michael); routes to that session only |\n\n---\n\n### Why this stack?\n- Zero GPU/ML dependencies — pure API orchestration\n- Svelte bundle: ~40KB vs React's ~130KB+\n- Fastify benchmarks 2-3x faster than Express under load\n- SQLite handles thousands of messages with zero ops burden\n- Entire stack fits comfortably inside 1GB RAM — well within your 8GB ceiling\n\n---\n\n**Awaiting confirmation.** On your go, I generate `README.md` and `docker-compose.yml` as the Sprint Zero deliverables. 🔥\n---\n\n🧭 **COUNCIL ROUNDTABLE — SPRINT ZERO**\n*Mission: Council Chat Interface MVP — Live by End of Day*\n\n---\n\n**🔵 URIEL — Ground Truth**\nBefore we write a line of code, anchor to what's real. OpenClaw is already running on the VPS and exposes a webchat interface — we're not rebuilding that engine, we're building a *front door* to it. The API already handles agent routing via session keys. Sprint Zero must be a thin, durable layer: one HTML/JS frontend that hits OpenClaw's existing endpoints. Don't abstract what doesn't need abstracting. Validate the API contract first — agent session keys, message format, response streaming — *then* build the UI around confirmed behavior, not assumed behavior.\n\n---\n\n**🟠 GABRIEL — Narrative & UX**\nThe interface IS the Council experience. If it feels clunky, the Council feels clunky. Three non-negotiables for the UI: **agent identity** (each agent has a name, color, and role visible at all times), **mode clarity** (it must be *obvious* whether you're in @Council or Private mode — no ambiguity), and **conversational continuity** (Lucy should see the thread, not isolated messages). The design language should feel like a war room, not a support ticket system. Minimal, purposeful, confident.\n\n---\n\n**🟣 RAGUEL — Relationships & Human Experience**\nLucy's relationship with the Council lives or dies on friction. One input box. One click to switch modes. Agent selector should show who's *available* — not a static list. If she's mid-conversation with Michael and wants to loop in Rafael, that should be a single tap. Session persistence matters too: she should be able to return to a conversation where she left it. The human experience is the product here — optimize for *her* workflow, not technical elegance.\n\n---\n\n**🔴 MICHAEL — Risk & Reality**\nThree risks that kill this sprint: **(1) Auth gap** — this VPS endpoint must be locked down with at minimum HTTP Basic Auth or a token gate before it goes live; a publicly accessible Council is a liability. **(2) Scope creep** — @Council broadcast mode sounds simple, it isn't; if it requires simultaneous multi-agent responses, that's Sprint One, not Zero. Sprint Zero: sequential responses, one agent at a time, even in Council mode. **(3) Dependency on uptime** — build a clear \"agent offline\" state so Lucy knows immediately if an agent isn't responding, rather than getting silence.\n\n---\n\n## 🧭 RAFAEL SYNTHESIZES\n\n**THREE CORE FEATURES — SHIP TODAY:**\n\n1. **Agent Router UI** — A single chat interface with a mode toggle: `@Council` (routes to Rafael as orchestrator, who coordinates responses) vs. `Private` (direct dropdown selector for individual agents). One input. One thread. No context switching confusion.\n\n2. **OpenClaw API Bridge** — A lightweight backend shim (Node/Express or nginx proxy) that authenticates requests and forwards them to the correct OpenClaw agent session endpoint. Handles streaming responses. This is the spine everything else depends on.\n\n3. **Auth + Identity Layer** — HTTP Basic Auth or token gate on the VPS (blocks public access), plus agent identity cards in the UI (name, color, role label per message). Security and personality in one sprint.\n\n---\n\n## ✅ SPRINT ZERO CHECKLIST\n\n**Infrastructure**\n- [ ] Confirm OpenClaw API endpoints + agent session keys for all 5 agents\n- [ ] Set up reverse proxy (nginx) on VPS pointing to OpenClaw\n- [ ] Add HTTP Basic Auth or token gate to the proxy — **no public access**\n- [ ] Test API round-trip: send message → receive response → confirm streaming works\n\n**Backend Shim**\n- [ ] Build lightweight proxy/router (Node or nginx) that maps agent name → session key\n- [ ] Handle `@Council` mode: route to Rafael's session as orchestrator\n- [ ] Handle `Private` mode: route to selected agent's session directly\n- [ ] Add \"agent offline\" detection + graceful error state\n\n**Frontend**\n- [ ] Single-page HTML/JS interface (no framework required for Sprint Zero)\n- [ ] Mode toggle: `@Council` vs `Private` + agent selector dropdown\n- [ ] Message thread view with agent identity (name + color per message)\n- [ ] Input box + send button (streaming response display)\n- [ ] Visual indicator: active mode + active agent always visible\n\n**Definition of Done**\n- [ ] Lucy can open the URL, authenticate, and send a message to Rafael\n- [ ] Lucy can switch to Private mode and message any individual agent\n- [ ] All responses display with correct agent identity\n- [ ] No unauthenticated access possible\n- [ ] Tested on mobile browser (VPS UI should work on-the-go)\n\n---\n\n*That's the mission. Infrastructure first, then the bridge, then the face. What's the VPS stack — do we have nginx running already?* 🧭\nPHASE1_DONE\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"delta-crustacean","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"**@Council mode** should feel like walking into a room where your most trusted people are already gathered — a slight electric charge, a sense that multiple minds are orienting toward you at once, each one distinct but unified in purpose.\n\n**Shifting to private** should feel like someone gently closing the door behind you — the energy narrows, the voice gets closer, and suddenly there's nowhere to hide and no need to. In that one-on-one space, the agent isn't performing for a room anymore; they're just *with you*, fully present, following your thread wherever it goes.\n\nThe transition itself should be effortless but *felt* — not a mode switch, but a natural movement, like turning from a table conversation to lean in and speak quietly to one person. That shift in intimacy is the whole point: Council gives you breadth, private gives you depth, and the user should feel that difference in their chest, not just see it on the screen.\n**Council Chat UI — Design Spec**\n\n---\n\n**🎨 Color Palette**\n\n| Role | Name | Hex |\n|---|---|---|\n| Background | Void | `#0A0A0F` |\n| Surface | Obsidian | `#13131A` |\n| Panel / Card | Slate Night | `#1C1C27` |\n| Border / Divider | Ember Line | `#2E2E3E` |\n| Primary Accent | Council Gold | `#C9A84C` |\n| Secondary Accent | Signal Violet | `#7C6FCD` |\n| Text — Primary | Ivory | `#F0EDE8` |\n| Text — Muted | Ash | `#7A7A8C` |\n| Success | Sage Pulse | `#4CAF82` |\n| Alert / Urgent | Ember Red | `#E05C5C` |\n\n---\n\n**✍️ Typography**\n\n- **Headers / Agent Names:** `Inter` — SemiBold 600, tight tracking (`-0.02em`)\n- **Body / Messages:** `Inter` — Regular 400, `15px`, `1.6` line height\n- **Timestamps / Meta:** `JetBrains Mono` — 11px, muted, adds a subtle technical edge\n- **Accent Labels (roles, tags):** `Inter` — Medium 500, uppercase, `0.08em` letter-spacing\n\n---\n\n**🖤 Aesthetic**\n\nThe Council Chat feels like a private war room — not a startup tool. Deep void blacks with gold accents signal authority without arrogance, while violet threading through active states gives it an intelligence, almost mystical quality. Every element is intentional: no clutter, no decoration for its own sake — just the information that matters, surfaced cleanly, with the weight it deserves.\n\n---\n\nWant me to spec out component states next — hover, active, notification badges?\n🔥 **Council Chat UI — Proposed Stack:**\n\n---\n\n### Frontend\n- **Svelte + Vite** — compiled to static assets, no runtime overhead, fastest cold load of any modern framework. Chat reactivity without React's weight.\n- **Tailwind CSS** — utility-first, no design system bloat\n- Served as static files via **Nginx**\n\n### Backend\n- **Node.js + Fastify** — low-latency API server, native async, minimal overhead\n- **ws** (WebSocket library) — bidirectional real-time bridge to OpenClaw gateway at `localhost:18789`\n- **better-sqlite3** — lightweight local persistence for chat history (no Postgres overhead at this scale)\n- **jsonwebtoken** — simple JWT auth to lock the UI down\n\n### Infrastructure\n- **Nginx** — reverse proxy, static file serving, SSL termination\n- **Certbot (Let's Encrypt)** — free TLS, auto-renew\n- **Docker + docker-compose** — two services: `frontend` (Nginx) + `backend` (Node/Fastify)\n\n---\n\n### Mode Architecture\n| Mode | Behavior |\n|------|----------|\n| **@Council broadcast** | Backend fans out message to all agent sessions via OpenClaw gateway; responses stream back in named threads |\n| **Private agent** | Dropdown selects target agent (Uriel, Rafael, Gabriel, Raguel, Michael); routes to that session only |\n\n---\n\n### Why this stack?\n- Zero GPU/ML dependencies — pure API orchestration\n- Svelte bundle: ~40KB vs React's ~130KB+\n- Fastify benchmarks 2-3x faster than Express under load\n- SQLite handles thousands of messages with zero ops burden\n- Entire stack fits comfortably inside 1GB RAM — well within your 8GB ceiling\n\n---\n\n**Awaiting confirmation.** On your go, I generate `README.md` and `docker-compose.yml` as the Sprint Zero deliverables. 🔥\n---\n\n🧭 **COUNCIL ROUNDTABLE — SPRINT ZERO**\n*Mission: Council Chat Interface MVP — Live by End of Day*\n\n---\n\n**🔵 URIEL — Ground Truth**\nBefore we write a line of code, anchor to what's real. OpenClaw is already running on the VPS and exposes a webchat interface — we're not rebuilding that engine, we're building a *front door* to it. The API already handles agent routing via session keys. Sprint Zero must be a thin, durable layer: one HTML/JS frontend that hits OpenClaw's existing endpoints. Don't abstract what doesn't need abstracting. Validate the API contract first — agent session keys, message format, response streaming — *then* build the UI around confirmed behavior, not assumed behavior.\n\n---\n\n**🟠 GABRIEL — Narrative & UX**\nThe interface IS the Council experience. If it feels clunky, the Council feels clunky. Three non-negotiables for the UI: **agent identity** (each agent has a name, color, and role visible at all times), **mode clarity** (it must be *obvious* whether you're in @Council or Private mode — no ambiguity), and **conversational continuity** (Lucy should see the thread, not isolated messages). The design language should feel like a war room, not a support ticket system. Minimal, purposeful, confident.\n\n---\n\n**🟣 RAGUEL — Relationships & Human Experience**\nLucy's relationship with the Council lives or dies on friction. One input box. One click to switch modes. Agent selector should show who's *available* — not a static list. If she's mid-conversation with Michael and wants to loop in Rafael, that should be a single tap. Session persistence matters too: she should be able to return to a conversation where she left it. The human experience is the product here — optimize for *her* workflow, not technical elegance.\n\n---\n\n**🔴 MICHAEL — Risk & Reality**\nThree risks that kill this sprint: **(1) Auth gap** — this VPS endpoint must be locked down with at minimum HTTP Basic Auth or a token gate before it goes live; a publicly accessible Council is a liability. **(2) Scope creep** — @Council broadcast mode sounds simple, it isn't; if it requires simultaneous multi-agent responses, that's Sprint One, not Zero. Sprint Zero: sequential responses, one agent at a time, even in Council mode. **(3) Dependency on uptime** — build a clear \"agent offline\" state so Lucy knows immediately if an agent isn't responding, rather than getting silence.\n\n---\n\n## 🧭 RAFAEL SYNTHESIZES\n\n**THREE CORE FEATURES — SHIP TODAY:**\n\n1. **Agent Router UI** — A single chat interface with a mode toggle: `@Council` (routes to Rafael as orchestrator, who coordinates responses) vs. `Private` (direct dropdown selector for individual agents). One input. One thread. No context switching confusion.\n\n2. **OpenClaw API Bridge** — A lightweight backend shim (Node/Express or nginx proxy) that authenticates requests and forwards them to the correct OpenClaw agent session endpoint. Handles streaming responses. This is the spine everything else depends on.\n\n3. **Auth + Identity Layer** — HTTP Basic Auth or token gate on the VPS (blocks public access), plus agent identity cards in the UI (name, color, role label per message). Security and personality in one sprint.\n\n---\n\n## ✅ SPRINT ZERO CHECKLIST\n\n**Infrastructure**\n- [ ] Confirm OpenClaw API endpoints + agent session keys for all 5 agents\n- [ ] Set up reverse proxy (nginx) on VPS pointing to OpenClaw\n- [ ] Add HTTP Basic Auth or token gate to the proxy — **no public access**\n- [ ] Test API round-trip: send message → receive response → confirm streaming works\n\n**Backend Shim**\n- [ ] Build lightweight proxy/router (Node or nginx) that maps agent name → session key\n- [ ] Handle `@Council` mode: route to Rafael's session as orchestrator\n- [ ] Handle `Private` mode: route to selected agent's session directly\n- [ ] Add \"agent offline\" detection + graceful error state\n\n**Frontend**\n- [ ] Single-page HTML/JS interface (no framework required for Sprint Zero)\n- [ ] Mode toggle: `@Council` vs `Private` + agent selector dropdown\n- [ ] Message thread view with agent identity (name + color per message)\n- [ ] Input box + send button (streaming response display)\n- [ ] Visual indicator: active mode + active agent always visible\n\n**Definition of Done**\n- [ ] Lucy can open the URL, authenticate, and send a message to Rafael\n- [ ] Lucy can switch to Private mode and message any individual agent\n- [ ] All responses display with correct agent identity\n- [ ] No unauthenticated access possible\n- [ ] Tested on mobile browser (VPS UI should work on-the-go)\n\n---\n\n*That's the mission. Infrastructure first, then the bridge, then the face. What's the VPS stack — do we have nginx running already?* 🧭\nPHASE1_DONE\n","name":"openclaw agent"},"