{"type":"message","id":"3a1ae726","parentId":"39dac3a8","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:02:48.667Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy has given the GO signal. I should now execute. The plan is:\n1. Generate the project structure\n2. Create docker-compose.yml and README.md\n3. Build the actual Council Room web interface\n\nSince Caddy is already running (not Nginx), I'll adapt Uriel's stack. Let me build this - I can do it directly since I have full access to the VPS.\n\nThe architecture:\n- Backend: Node.js + Fastify, bridges to OpenClaw gateway at localhost:18789\n- Frontend: Single HTML file (simpler for Sprint Zero, no build step needed)\n- Auth: Simple token/password gate\n- Caddy: Already running, I'll add a route for /council\n\n\n- Skip Docker for now since Caddy is already running and it adds unnecessary complexity\n\nNow I need to understand the OpenClaw API at localhost:18789 to figure out how to make requests to agents.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"GO. Executing now — building the full Council Room."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_RVxWZTxz8RIlNfUhrsd7OA","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check OpenClaw gateway API\ncurl -s http://localhost:18789/ 2>&1 | head -20\ncurl -s http://localhost:18789/health 2>&1 | head -10"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":394,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":114980,"totalTokens":115377,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.00591,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.43117500000000003,"total":0.43709400000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772982158505}}
