{"type":"message","id":"fe51d1fb","parentId":"f3580915","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:06:27.452Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] **Council Room is live.** 🛡️\n\n---\n\n**🔗 https://64.227.110.70/council**\n**🔑 Token: `council-88d2f8242c07fcef`**\n\n---\n\n**What's built:**\n\n- **@Council mode** — broadcasts to Rafael who coordinates the full Council\n- **Private mode** — direct one-on-one with any agent (Rafael, Uriel, Michael, Gabriel, Raguel)\n- **Dark war room aesthetic** — Void black, Council Gold, Signal Violet, JetBrains Mono timestamps\n- **Mode transition** — smooth toggle between Council broadcast and Private intimacy\n- **Chat history** — persists in localStorage, survives page refresh\n- **WebSocket** — real-time connection, auto-reconnects\n- **Auth token gate** — no public access\n\n**Architecture:**\n- Node.js backend bridging to OpenClaw gateway\n- Served through Caddy with TLS\n- Auto-restarts on reboot via crontab\n\nOpen it, enter the token, and send your first message. 🚀"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":266,"cacheRead":129256,"cacheWrite":348,"totalTokens":129871,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.0039900000000000005,"cacheRead":0.0387768,"cacheWrite":0.001305,"total":0.044074800000000004}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772982380074}}
{"type":"message","id":"cff9c71a","parentId":"fe51d1fb","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:08:17.056Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[media attached: /home/openclaw/.openclaw/media/inbound/file_0---73a7e235-b4f6-4989-b2a6-7d3f477901bf.jpg (image/jpeg) | /home/openclaw/.openclaw/media/inbound/file_0---73a7e235-b4f6-4989-b2a6-7d3f477901bf.jpg]\nTo send an image back, prefer the message tool (media/path/filePath). If you must inline, use MEDIA:https://example.com/image.jpg (spaces ok, quote if needed) or a safe relative path like MEDIA:./image.jpg. Avoid absolute paths (MEDIA:/...) and ~ paths — they are blocked for security. Keep caption in the text body.\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"69\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 15:08 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nwhat is this rundl bla bla bla , and why only Raphael talking"},{"type":"image","data":"","mimeType":"image/jpeg"}],"timestamp":1772982497043}}
{"type":"message","id":"43186a76","parentId":"cff9c71a","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:08:42.226Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Two issues to fix:\n\n1. **The JSON blob** - The backend is returning the raw JSON from OpenClaw CLI (`--json` flag) instead of parsing the reply text out of it. I need to fix the backend to extract the actual text from the JSON response.\n\n2. **Only Rafael talking** - In @Council mode, only Rafael is responding. This is by design in Sprint Zero (sequential), but Lucy wants all agents to respond. I need to make @Council mode fan out to all agents and display each response.\n\nLet me fix both:\n\n1. Fix the JSON parsing in the backend - the response has `result.payloads[0].text` \n2. Fix @Council to fan out to all agents\n\n\n3. For the @Council mode, I'll need to trigger all 5 agents in parallel and stream their responses back as they complete, rather than waiting for just the first one.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Two bugs — I see them. Fixing both now:\n\n1. **Raw JSON showing** — backend not parsing the response correctly\n2. **Only Rafael** — @Council should fan out to all 5 agents"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_HghBlRbbLm3YGT0L6BxI9Y","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import Fastify from 'fastify';\nimport cors from '@fastify/cors';\nimport websocket from '@fastify/websocket';\nimport { spawn } from 'child_process';\nimport { createHash } from 'crypto';\n\nconst fastify = Fastify({ logger: false });\nawait fastify.register(cors, { origin: true });\nawait fastify.register(websocket);\n\nconst AUTH_TOKEN = process.env.COUNCIL_TOKEN || 'council-88d2f8242c07fcef';\n\nconsole.log(`🛡️  Council Room API starting...`);\nconsole.log(`🔑  Auth token: ${AUTH_TOKEN}`);\n\nconst AGENTS = {\n  rafael:  { name: 'Rafael',  emoji: '🧭', role: 'The Guide'        },\n  uriel:   { name: 'Uriel',   emoji: '🔥', role: \"God's Fire\"       },\n  michael: { name: 'Michael', emoji: '🛡️', role: 'The Wise Advisor' },\n  gabriel: { name: 'Gabriel', emoji: '📣', role: 'The Voice'        },\n  raguel:  { name: 'Raguel',  emoji: '🤝', role: 'The Friend'       },\n};\n\n// Run openclaw agent — returns clean text reply\nfunction runAgent(agentId, message) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    // Use main agent for \"michael\" since that's the actual id\n    const actualId = agentId === 'michael' ? 'main' : agentId;\n    const args = ['agent', '--agent', actualId, '--message', message, '--json'];\n    const proc = spawn('openclaw', args, {\n      env: { ...process.env, HOME: '/home/openclaw' }\n    });\n\n    let buffer = '';\n    proc.stdout.on('data', (chunk) => { buffer += chunk.toString(); });\n    proc.on('close', () => {\n      try {\n        const json = JSON.parse(buffer);\n        // Extract text from payloads\n        const text = json?.result?.payloads?.[0]?.text\n          || json?.reply\n          || json?.text\n          || json?.message\n          || buffer.trim();\n        resolve(text);\n      } catch {\n        resolve(buffer.trim());\n      }\n    });\n    proc.on('error', (err) => resolve(`Error: ${err.message}`));\n  });\n}\n\n// Auth check\nfunction checkAuth(req, reply) {\n  const token = req.headers['x-council-token'] || req.query?.token;\n  if (token !== AUTH_TOKEN) { reply.code(401).send({ error: 'Unauthorized' }); return false; }\n  return true;\n}\n\nfastify.get('/agents', async (req, reply) => {\n  if (!checkAuth(req, reply)) return;\n  return { agents: AGENTS };\n});\n\nfastify.get('/health', async (req, reply) => {\n  if (!checkAuth(req, reply)) return;\n  return { status: 'ok', agents: Object.keys(AGENTS) };\n});\n\n// WebSocket — real-time\nfastify.get('/ws', { websocket: true }, (socket, req) => {\n  const token = new URL(req.url, 'http://localhost').searchParams.get('token');\n  if (token !== AUTH_TOKEN) {\n    socket.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Unauthorized' }));\n    socket.close();\n    return;\n  }\n\n  const send = (data) => {\n    if (socket.readyState === 1) socket.send(JSON.stringify(data));\n  };\n\n  send({ type: 'connected', message: 'Council Room connected' });\n\n  socket.on('message', async (raw) => {\n    let data;\n    try { data = JSON.parse(raw.toString()); } catch { return; }\n    const { agentId, message, mode } = data;\n    if (!message) return;\n\n    if (mode === 'council') {\n      // Fan out to ALL 5 agents simultaneously\n      const agentIds = Object.keys(AGENTS);\n      const councilPrompt = `${message}`;\n\n      // Send all thinking indicators\n      agentIds.forEach(id => send({ type: 'thinking', agentId: id, agent: AGENTS[id] }));\n\n      // Run all agents in parallel\n      const promises = agentIds.map(async (id) => {\n        const response = await runAgent(id, councilPrompt);\n        send({ type: 'response', agentId: id, agent: AGENTS[id], response });\n      });\n\n      await Promise.all(promises);\n      send({ type: 'council_done' });\n\n    } else {\n      // Private — single agent\n      const targetId = agentId || 'rafael';\n      send({ type: 'thinking', agentId: targetId, agent: AGENTS[targetId] });\n      const response = await runAgent(targetId, message);\n      send({ type: 'response', agentId: targetId, agent: AGENTS[targetId], response });\n    }\n  });\n});\n\nconst PORT = parseInt(process.env.PORT || '3001');\nawait fastify.listen({ port: PORT, host: '127.0.0.1' });\nconsole.log(`✅  Council Room API on http://127.0.0.1:${PORT}`);\n","file_path":"/home/openclaw/council-room/backend/server.js"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":1772,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":130980,"totalTokens":132755,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.02658,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.49117500000000003,"total":0.517764}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772982497049}}
