{"type":"message","id":"8042720b","parentId":"8fd53c9d","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:24:31.207Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"From the screenshots I can see:\n\n1. The Council Room UI is working - private mode, agent picker on mobile, separate panes per agent ✅\n2. The secret key is **\"Watermelon\"** - Lucy told Rafael in the Private chat\n3. There's a bug - Rafael's response appeared in the Uriel pane (cross-contamination between panes)\n4. Lucy wants a memory feature like Gemini - ability to start a new chat but retain context from old ones\n\nThe cross-pane contamination bug: When Lucy sent the message to Rafael, Rafael's response showed up in Uriel's pane. This is a routing bug in the backend - the response comes back to whatever pane is currently active, not necessarily the one where the message was sent.\n \nFor the memory feature, I need to persist chat history server-side so agents can reference previous conversations when starting new ones. To fix the routing bug, I'll tag each WebSocket message with the target pane ID so responses land in the correct agent's pane regardless of which one's currently active.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Got it — secret key is **\"Watermelon\"** 🍉 (saw it in your Rafael private chat screenshot).\n\nAlso spotted two things to fix:\n1. **Cross-pane bug** — Rafael's response showed up in Uriel's pane when you switched\n2. **Memory feature** — new chat but agents retain context\n\nFixing the routing bug first, then adding memory:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_zObSxdzEsr6awbSnJrbcVI","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import Fastify from 'fastify';\nimport cors from '@fastify/cors';\nimport websocket from '@fastify/websocket';\nimport { spawn } from 'child_process';\nimport { createHash } from 'crypto';\nimport { existsSync, readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'fs';\n\nconst fastify = Fastify({ logger: false });\nawait fastify.register(cors, { origin: true });\nawait fastify.register(websocket);\n\nconst AUTH_TOKEN = process.env.COUNCIL_TOKEN || 'council-88d2f8242c07fcef';\nconst MEMORY_FILE = '/home/openclaw/council-room/memory.json';\n\nconsole.log(`🛡️  Council Room API starting...`);\n\nconst AGENTS = {\n  rafael:  { name: 'Rafael',  emoji: '🧭', role: 'The Guide'        },\n  uriel:   { name: 'Uriel',   emoji: '🔥', role: \"God's Fire\"       },\n  michael: { name: 'Michael', emoji: '🛡️', role: 'The Wise Advisor' },\n  gabriel: { name: 'Gabriel', emoji: '📣', role: 'The Voice'        },\n  raguel:  { name: 'Raguel',  emoji: '🤝', role: 'The Friend'       },\n};\n\n// ── MEMORY (persisted to disk) ──\nfunction loadMemory() {\n  try { return JSON.parse(readFileSync(MEMORY_FILE, 'utf8')); } catch { return { facts: [], sessions: [] }; }\n}\nfunction saveMemory(mem) {\n  writeFileSync(MEMORY_FILE, JSON.stringify(mem, null, 2));\n}\n\n// ── AGENT RUNNER ──\nfunction runAgent(agentId, message) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const actualId = agentId === 'michael' ? 'main' : agentId;\n    const args = ['agent', '--agent', actualId, '--message', message, '--json'];\n    const proc = spawn('openclaw', args, { env: { ...process.env, HOME: '/home/openclaw' } });\n    let buffer = '';\n    proc.stdout.on('data', c => buffer += c.toString());\n    proc.on('close', () => {\n      try {\n        const json = JSON.parse(buffer);\n        resolve(json?.result?.payloads?.[0]?.text || json?.reply || json?.text || buffer.trim());\n      } catch { resolve(buffer.trim()); }\n    });\n    proc.on('error', e => resolve(`Error: ${e.message}`));\n  });\n}\n\nfunction checkAuth(req, reply) {\n  const token = req.headers['x-council-token'] || req.query?.token;\n  if (token !== AUTH_TOKEN) { reply.code(401).send({ error: 'Unauthorized' }); return false; }\n  return true;\n}\n\n// ── REST ENDPOINTS ──\nfastify.get('/health', async (req, reply) => {\n  if (!checkAuth(req, reply)) return;\n  return { status: 'ok', agents: Object.keys(AGENTS) };\n});\n\n// GET /memory — return all saved facts\nfastify.get('/memory', async (req, reply) => {\n  if (!checkAuth(req, reply)) return;\n  return loadMemory();\n});\n\n// POST /memory — save a fact\nfastify.post('/memory', async (req, reply) => {\n  if (!checkAuth(req, reply)) return;\n  const { fact } = req.body;\n  if (!fact) return reply.code(400).send({ error: 'fact required' });\n  const mem = loadMemory();\n  mem.facts.push({ fact, ts: Date.now(), date: new Date().toISOString() });\n  saveMemory(mem);\n  return { ok: true, total: mem.facts.length };\n});\n\n// DELETE /memory/:index — remove a fact\nfastify.delete('/memory/:idx', async (req, reply) => {\n  if (!checkAuth(req, reply)) return;\n  const mem = loadMemory();\n  const idx = parseInt(req.params.idx);\n  if (idx >= 0 && idx < mem.facts.length) mem.facts.splice(idx, 1);\n  saveMemory(mem);\n  return { ok: true, total: mem.facts.length };\n});\n\n// ── WEBSOCKET ──\nfastify.get('/ws', { websocket: true }, (socket, req) => {\n  const token = new URL(req.url, 'http://localhost').searchParams.get('token');\n  if (token !== AUTH_TOKEN) { socket.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Unauthorized' })); socket.close(); return; }\n\n  const send = d => { if (socket.readyState === 1) socket.send(JSON.stringify(d)); };\n  send({ type: 'connected' });\n\n  socket.on('message', async (raw) => {\n    let data; try { data = JSON.parse(raw.toString()); } catch { return; }\n    const { agentId, message, mode, pane, sessionId } = data;\n    if (!message) return;\n\n    // Build context from memory\n    const mem = loadMemory();\n    let memCtx = '';\n    if (mem.facts.length > 0) {\n      memCtx = `\\n\\n[Memory context from Lucy]:\\n${mem.facts.map(f => `- ${f.fact}`).join('\\n')}`;\n    }\n\n    if (mode === 'council') {\n      const agentIds = Object.keys(AGENTS);\n      // Send thinking with pane tag\n      agentIds.forEach(id => send({ type: 'thinking', agentId: id, agent: AGENTS[id], pane: 'council', sessionId }));\n\n      await Promise.all(agentIds.map(async id => {\n        const response = await runAgent(id, message + memCtx);\n        send({ type: 'response', agentId: id, agent: AGENTS[id], response, pane: 'council', sessionId });\n      }));\n      send({ type: 'council_done', pane: 'council', sessionId });\n\n    } else {\n      const targetId = agentId || 'rafael';\n      // CRITICAL: echo back the pane so frontend routes correctly\n      send({ type: 'thinking', agentId: targetId, agent: AGENTS[targetId], pane, sessionId });\n      const response = await runAgent(targetId, message + memCtx);\n      send({ type: 'response', agentId: targetId, agent: AGENTS[targetId], response, pane, sessionId });\n    }\n  });\n});\n\nconst PORT = parseInt(process.env.PORT || '3001');\nawait fastify.listen({ port: PORT, host: '127.0.0.1' });\nconsole.log(`✅  Council Room API on http://127.0.0.1:${PORT}`);\n","file_path":"/home/openclaw/council-room/backend/server.js"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":2309,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":153080,"totalTokens":155392,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.034635,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.5740500000000001,"total":0.6086940000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772983433596}}
