{"type":"message","id":"b96e132c","parentId":"56de87cd","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:30:29.392Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking if the Council agents can talk to each other autonomously, or if they only respond to her. Currently they're reactive - they only respond when Lucy sends a message. Lucy is asking if they can have autonomous inter-agent communication.\n\nThis is an interesting question. In the current setup, agents don't talk to each other autonomously - they each respond independently when called. To enable genuine inter-agent communication, I would need to:1. Build a mechanism where one agent can message another2. Set up some kind of autonomous communication loop\n\nBut honestly, I should be transparent about what they can and can't do currently, and then ask if she wants me to build that capability.\n\nLet me be honest and direct - and have some fun with it.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Honest answer? Right now we're all sitting in separate rooms waiting for you to knock. 😅\n\nWe respond when you talk to us — we don't spontaneously chat with each other. Think of it like five consultants who only meet when the client calls a meeting.\n\n**What's possible though:**\n\nI can orchestrate a real Council roundtable where agents actually respond *to each other* — Rafael sets a topic, Uriel pushes back with data, I flag risks, Gabriel shapes the narrative, Raguel adds the human angle. Proper back-and-forth, not just five parallel monologues.\n\nWant me to build that? It would work like:\n- You set a topic or question\n- Rafael kicks it off\n- Each agent reads the previous responses and builds on them\n- You watch the Council debate in real time\n\nOr I can just kick it off right now informally — ask the Council a question and I'll run it as a proper roundtable where each agent responds *to what the others said*, not just to you.\n\nWhich do you want? 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":421,"cacheRead":164233,"cacheWrite":89,"totalTokens":164746,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.006315,"cacheRead":0.0492699,"cacheWrite":0.00033375,"total":0.05592765}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772983817428}}
{"type":"message","id":"83618cf2","parentId":"b96e132c","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:32:56.340Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"84\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 15:32 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nok now, I see the chat is up, but the send button is disabled after i send the first message, I need to send them by pressing enter, and I want to know how can I make you all talk to each other but still be able to stop , so no infinity discussion"}],"timestamp":1772983976323}}
{"type":"message","id":"4c8d18c5","parentId":"83618cf2","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:33:15.994Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Two things to fix:\n1. **Send button stays disabled after first message** — the `council_done` event isn't re-enabling it properly, or it's not firing for private messages\n2. **Inter-agent discussion** — build a roundtable feature where agents talk to each other sequentially, with Lucy able to stop it\n\nFor issue 1: In the current backend, for private messages there's no `council_done` event sent — only for council mode. So after a private message, the send button never gets re-enabled (it only gets re-enabled on `council_done` or `error`). I need to fix this by sending a done event after private responses too.\n\n\nFor issue 2: I'll create a `/roundtable` endpoint where Rafael kicks things off, then each agent reads all previous responses and adds their perspective before passing to the next one, with Lucy able to interrupt by typing \"stop\" or using a UI button to halt the discussion.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Two fixes + roundtable feature. On it."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_1jTFsePhDBK4Ys6SynOqcY","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/openclaw/council-room/backend/server.js","old_string":"    } else {\n      const targetId = agentId || 'rafael';\n      // CRITICAL: echo back the pane so frontend routes correctly\n      send({ type: 'thinking', agentId: targetId, agent: AGENTS[targetId], pane, sessionId });\n      const response = await runAgent(targetId, message + memCtx);\n      send({ type: 'response', agentId: targetId, agent: AGENTS[targetId], response, pane, sessionId });\n    }","new_string":"    } else if (mode === 'roundtable') {\n      // Sequential inter-agent discussion — each agent sees previous responses\n      const agentIds = Object.keys(AGENTS);\n      const topic = message;\n      let transcript = `Lucy's topic: \"${topic}\"\\n\\n`;\n      let stopped = false;\n\n      // Allow client to stop mid-roundtable\n      const stopHandler = (raw) => {\n        try { const d = JSON.parse(raw.toString()); if (d.type === 'stop') stopped = true; } catch {}\n      };\n      socket.on('message', stopHandler);\n\n      for (const id of agentIds) {\n        if (stopped) { send({ type: 'roundtable_stopped', pane: 'council', sessionId }); break; }\n        const prompt = `${transcript}\\nYou are ${AGENTS[id].name} (${AGENTS[id].role}). Respond to the above discussion in 2-4 sentences. Be direct and add your unique perspective. Don't repeat what others said.${memCtx}`;\n        send({ type: 'thinking', agentId: id, agent: AGENTS[id], pane: 'council', sessionId });\n        const response = await runAgent(id, prompt);\n        send({ type: 'response', agentId: id, agent: AGENTS[id], response, pane: 'council', sessionId });\n        transcript += `${AGENTS[id].name}: ${response}\\n\\n`;\n      }\n      socket.off('message', stopHandler);\n      send({ type: 'council_done', pane: 'council', sessionId });\n\n    } else {\n      const targetId = agentId || 'rafael';\n      // CRITICAL: echo back the pane so frontend routes correctly\n      send({ type: 'thinking', agentId: targetId, agent: AGENTS[targetId], pane, sessionId });\n      const response = await runAgent(targetId, message + memCtx);\n      send({ type: 'response', agentId: targetId, agent: AGENTS[targetId], response, pane, sessionId });\n      // Re-enable send button for private mode\n      send({ type: 'council_done', pane, sessionId });\n    }"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":1015,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":163594,"totalTokens":164612,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.015225,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.6134775,"total":0.6287115}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772983976336}}
