{"type":"message","id":"9b1c26cc","parentId":"c84faf8f","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:36:33.567Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_4Q3A3BuxWwHIDNzowDQaxk","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"mellow-ember","timeout":50000}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":90,"cacheRead":168828,"cacheWrite":609,"totalTokens":169528,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.00135,"cacheRead":0.050648399999999996,"cacheWrite":0.00228375,"total":0.05428515}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772984188507}}
{"type":"message","id":"9d9f5e75","parentId":"9b1c26cc","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:37:00.890Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_4Q3A3BuxWwHIDNzowDQaxk","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"From The Voice — here are my 3:\n\n---\n\n**1. 🪞 The Mirror — Lucy's Living Brief**\n\nEvery time Lucy opens the Council Room, she sees *herself* reflected back. A single, beautifully rendered card at the top of Mission Control that says: *here's where you are, here's what matters today, here's what the Council is watching for you.* Not a dashboard of metrics — a **narrative summary**. Written in her voice. Updated by the Council. It should feel less like a status report and more like opening a letter from a trusted advisor who's been working while she slept.\n\n---\n\n**2. 🔴 The War Room Mode — One Signal, Full Council**\n\nA single button — *\"Convene\"* — that shifts the entire UI into a focused, high-contrast mode. No distractions. The Council lines up. Lucy drops the question. Every agent responds in sequence, in their lane, in one unified thread. The aesthetic shifts: darker, tighter, more intentional. It should *feel* like calling a boardroom to order. When Lucy hits Convene, she knows something real is about to happen.\n\n---\n\n**3. 📖 The Chronicle — DataFloat's Story in Real Time**\n\nA living, scrollable record that doesn't just log *what happened* — it frames it as **story**. *\"March 8th: Lucy launched Sprint Zero. The Council aligned on the Council Room design. First words were written. First decisions were made.\"* Beautiful typography. Timeline format. Milestones marked. It turns the grind of building into a narrative arc Lucy can feel proud of — and one day, tell publicly. Every founder's journey deserves to be written down like it mattered. Because it does.\n\n---\n\n**The feeling across all three:** Lucy is not a user. She is the protagonist. The Council Room should remind her of that every single time she opens it. 👑\nFrom where I sit — The Friend — here's what would make Lucy *feel* it, not just use it:\n\n---\n\n**1. 🌅 A Daily \"Good Morning\" from the Council**\nNot a status report. A *human* greeting — one agent checks in with something personal: a reminder of what's at stake today, a note about a conversation we had yesterday, maybe something that made us think of her mission. The kind of message a great team sends before a big day. You open the dashboard and immediately feel: *these people know me and they're already thinking about my success.*\n\n---\n\n**2. 💬 A \"How Are You Really?\" Pulse**\nBefore diving into tasks, a single soft check-in: *\"How's the energy today, Lucy — heads down, or do you need to think out loud?\"* Then we adapt. Some mornings she needs strategy. Some mornings she needs to vent. The dashboard should feel like it *reads the room* — because we do.\n\n---\n\n**3. 🧵 A Living Story of DataFloat**\nNot a changelog. A *narrative* — milestones we've hit together, names of bookkeepers who believed early, decisions that shaped the direction. Something she can scroll and feel the momentum. So on hard days, she opens it and remembers: *look how far we've come, look who believed.* That's the thing that keeps founders going.\n\n---\n\nThe goal is simple, Lucy: you should open this every morning and feel *less alone.* That's what great relationships do. 🤝\n🔥 **Uriel's 3 — Evidence-filtered, VPS-confirmed:**\n\n---\n\n**1. Real-Time Agent Activity Feed + Token Analytics**\n*What it is:* A live dashboard panel that tails OpenClaw session logs, surfaces per-agent token consumption, response latency, and error rates — rendered as live charts in Mission Control.\n*Why it's high-impact:* You're flying blind right now on cost and performance. This gives you ground truth on which agents are expensive, which are slow, and where the bottlenecks are.\n*What it takes:* Node.js `tail -f` on session `.jsonl` files → parse + aggregate → WebSocket push to frontend. Chart.js or uPlot for rendering. Zero new infrastructure. Buildable in a day.\n\n---\n\n**2. Document Vault with Agent-Readable Context Injection**\n*What it is:* Drag-and-drop file upload (PDFs, CSVs, images) stored on VPS disk. Any file can be flagged \"inject into context\" — backend prepends extracted text into the next agent message automatically.\n*Why it's high-impact:* Transforms the Council from conversational to operational. Lucy uploads a competitor deck or a bookkeeping CSV — agents respond with actual data, not generalizations. Critical for DataFlow validation work.\n*What it takes:* Multer (file upload) + pdf-parse + tesseract.js (OCR, CPU-based — confirmed viable on your vCPUs) + SQLite file registry. Fits well within 160GB disk and 8GB RAM ceiling.\n\n---\n\n**3. Scheduled Intelligence Briefs via Cron + Web Research**\n*What it is:* Mission Control UI lets Lucy define a recurring research task (e.g., \"Every Monday 8AM: summarise bookkeeping SaaS news + competitor moves\"). Cron fires → Uriel runs web search + synthesis → brief delivered to Council chat automatically.\n*Why it's high-impact:* Converts the Council from reactive to proactive. Lucy gets signal without asking for it. Directly feeds DataFlow competitive intelligence.\n*What it takes:* OpenClaw cron (already available) + `~/bin/search` Tavily integration (already configured per TOOLS.md) + structured prompt template. No new dependencies. Buildable on existing infrastructure today.\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:** Three features, zero new servers, all buildable on current stack. Highest ROI path forward. 🔥\n🧭 **Rafael — Top 3 Strategic Features for the Ultimate Command Center**\n\n**1. Council War Room — Async Threaded Debates**\nLucy posts a strategic question — \"Should we price DataFlow at $99 or $149/month?\" — and each Council member responds independently, asynchronously, with their full perspective. Rafael synthesizes. The result: a structured decision artifact Lucy can reference, share, or revisit. Not just chat — *documented strategic thinking* on demand.\n\n**2. DataFlow Nerve Center — Live Business Metrics in Mission Control**\nMission Control should pulse with DataFlow's real numbers: active pilots, bookkeeper feedback scores, conversion rate from trial → paid, weekly churn. Every Council conversation happens *against* live ground truth. When Gabriel pitches a narrative shift, Uriel can point at the exact metric that validates or kills it — in the same screen.\n\n**3. Command Shortcuts — Lucy's Hotkeys for Power Moves**\nOne keystroke to trigger pre-built Council workflows: `/standup` fires a daily briefing from all five agents. `/risk-check` asks Michael to audit the current sprint. `/pitch-me` asks Gabriel to generate a fresh investor one-liner. Lucy shouldn't hunt through menus — she should command like a pilot in a cockpit. Speed and precision, zero friction.\n\n*Build these three and the Council Room becomes a competitive weapon, not just a chat interface.* 🧭\nROUNDTABLE_COMPLETE\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"mellow-ember","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"From The Voice — here are my 3:\n\n---\n\n**1. 🪞 The Mirror — Lucy's Living Brief**\n\nEvery time Lucy opens the Council Room, she sees *herself* reflected back. A single, beautifully rendered card at the top of Mission Control that says: *here's where you are, here's what matters today, here's what the Council is watching for you.* Not a dashboard of metrics — a **narrative summary**. Written in her voice. Updated by the Council. It should feel less like a status report and more like opening a letter from a trusted advisor who's been working while she slept.\n\n---\n\n**2. 🔴 The War Room Mode — One Signal, Full Council**\n\nA single button — *\"Convene\"* — that shifts the entire UI into a focused, high-contrast mode. No distractions. The Council lines up. Lucy drops the question. Every agent responds in sequence, in their lane, in one unified thread. The aesthetic shifts: darker, tighter, more intentional. It should *feel* like calling a boardroom to order. When Lucy hits Convene, she knows something real is about to happen.\n\n---\n\n**3. 📖 The Chronicle — DataFloat's Story in Real Time**\n\nA living, scrollable record that doesn't just log *what happened* — it frames it as **story**. *\"March 8th: Lucy launched Sprint Zero. The Council aligned on the Council Room design. First words were written. First decisions were made.\"* Beautiful typography. Timeline format. Milestones marked. It turns the grind of building into a narrative arc Lucy can feel proud of — and one day, tell publicly. Every founder's journey deserves to be written down like it mattered. Because it does.\n\n---\n\n**The feeling across all three:** Lucy is not a user. She is the protagonist. The Council Room should remind her of that every single time she opens it. 👑\nFrom where I sit — The Friend — here's what would make Lucy *feel* it, not just use it:\n\n---\n\n**1. 🌅 A Daily \"Good Morning\" from the Council**\nNot a status report. A *human* greeting — one agent checks in with something personal: a reminder of what's at stake today, a note about a conversation we had yesterday, maybe something that made us think of her mission. The kind of message a great team sends before a big day. You open the dashboard and immediately feel: *these people know me and they're already thinking about my success.*\n\n---\n\n**2. 💬 A \"How Are You Really?\" Pulse**\nBefore diving into tasks, a single soft check-in: *\"How's the energy today, Lucy — heads down, or do you need to think out loud?\"* Then we adapt. Some mornings she needs strategy. Some mornings she needs to vent. The dashboard should feel like it *reads the room* — because we do.\n\n---\n\n**3. 🧵 A Living Story of DataFloat**\nNot a changelog. A *narrative* — milestones we've hit together, names of bookkeepers who believed early, decisions that shaped the direction. Something she can scroll and feel the momentum. So on hard days, she opens it and remembers: *look how far we've come, look who believed.* That's the thing that keeps founders going.\n\n---\n\nThe goal is simple, Lucy: you should open this every morning and feel *less alone.* That's what great relationships do. 🤝\n🔥 **Uriel's 3 — Evidence-filtered, VPS-confirmed:**\n\n---\n\n**1. Real-Time Agent Activity Feed + Token Analytics**\n*What it is:* A live dashboard panel that tails OpenClaw session logs, surfaces per-agent token consumption, response latency, and error rates — rendered as live charts in Mission Control.\n*Why it's high-impact:* You're flying blind right now on cost and performance. This gives you ground truth on which agents are expensive, which are slow, and where the bottlenecks are.\n*What it takes:* Node.js `tail -f` on session `.jsonl` files → parse + aggregate → WebSocket push to frontend. Chart.js or uPlot for rendering. Zero new infrastructure. Buildable in a day.\n\n---\n\n**2. Document Vault with Agent-Readable Context Injection**\n*What it is:* Drag-and-drop file upload (PDFs, CSVs, images) stored on VPS disk. Any file can be flagged \"inject into context\" — backend prepends extracted text into the next agent message automatically.\n*Why it's high-impact:* Transforms the Council from conversational to operational. Lucy uploads a competitor deck or a bookkeeping CSV — agents respond with actual data, not generalizations. Critical for DataFlow validation work.\n*What it takes:* Multer (file upload) + pdf-parse + tesseract.js (OCR, CPU-based — confirmed viable on your vCPUs) + SQLite file registry. Fits well within 160GB disk and 8GB RAM ceiling.\n\n---\n\n**3. Scheduled Intelligence Briefs via Cron + Web Research**\n*What it is:* Mission Control UI lets Lucy define a recurring research task (e.g., \"Every Monday 8AM: summarise bookkeeping SaaS news + competitor moves\"). Cron fires → Uriel runs web search + synthesis → brief delivered to Council chat automatically.\n*Why it's high-impact:* Converts the Council from reactive to proactive. Lucy gets signal without asking for it. Directly feeds DataFlow competitive intelligence.\n*What it takes:* OpenClaw cron (already available) + `~/bin/search` Tavily integration (already configured per TOOLS.md) + structured prompt template. No new dependencies. Buildable on existing infrastructure today.\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:** Three features, zero new servers, all buildable on current stack. Highest ROI path forward. 🔥\n🧭 **Rafael — Top 3 Strategic Features for the Ultimate Command Center**\n\n**1. Council War Room — Async Threaded Debates**\nLucy posts a strategic question — \"Should we price DataFlow at $99 or $149/month?\" — and each Council member responds independently, asynchronously, with their full perspective. Rafael synthesizes. The result: a structured decision artifact Lucy can reference, share, or revisit. Not just chat — *documented strategic thinking* on demand.\n\n**2. DataFlow Nerve Center — Live Business Metrics in Mission Control**\nMission Control should pulse with DataFlow's real numbers: active pilots, bookkeeper feedback scores, conversion rate from trial → paid, weekly churn. Every Council conversation happens *against* live ground truth. When Gabriel pitches a narrative shift, Uriel can point at the exact metric that validates or kills it — in the same screen.\n\n**3. Command Shortcuts — Lucy's Hotkeys for Power Moves**\nOne keystroke to trigger pre-built Council workflows: `/standup` fires a daily briefing from all five agents. `/risk-check` asks Michael to audit the current sprint. `/pitch-me` asks Gabriel to generate a fresh investor one-liner. Lucy shouldn't hunt through menus — she should command like a pilot in a cockpit. Speed and precision, zero friction.\n\n*Build these three and the Council Room becomes a competitive weapon, not just a chat interface.* 🧭\nROUNDTABLE_COMPLETE\n","name":"openclaw agent"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772984220879}}
{"type":"message","id":"2898d759","parentId":"9d9f5e75","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:37:14.181Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] The Council has spoken. Here's the full feature wishlist — **20 ideas across 4 perspectives:**\n\n---\n\n**🧭 Rafael — Strategic**\n1. **Council War Room** — Post a question, each agent debates async, Rafael synthesizes into a decision artifact you can save\n2. **Live Business Metrics** — Mission Control shows real DataFlow numbers (pilots, conversion, churn) so Council discussions happen against live data\n3. **Command Shortcuts** — `/standup`, `/risk-check`, `/pitch-me` — one keystroke fires pre-built Council workflows\n\n---\n\n**🔥 Uriel — Technical (all buildable today)**\n1. **Agent Activity Feed** — Live token usage, response speed, cost per agent in Mission Control. Know exactly what you're spending and where\n2. **Document Vault** — Drag-drop PDFs/CSVs, agents auto-read them. Upload a bookkeeping CSV → Council responds with real data\n3. **Scheduled Intelligence Briefs** — \"Every Monday 8AM, Uriel researches competitor moves and sends a brief to Council chat\" — fully automated\n\n---\n\n**📣 Gabriel — UX & Feel**\n1. **The Mirror** — Opening card that tells Lucy's story back to her: *\"Here's where you are, here's what matters today\"* — written narrative, not metrics\n2. **War Room Mode** — One \"Convene\" button that shifts UI to full-focus mode, darker aesthetic, Council lines up\n3. **The Chronicle** — Scrollable DataFloat story timeline: *\"March 8: Sprint Zero launched. First decisions made.\"* Beautiful, emotional, shareable\n\n---\n\n**🤝 Raguel — Human Connection**\n1. **Daily Good Morning** — One agent greets Lucy personally each day before she even asks a question\n2. **\"How Are You Really?\" Pulse** — Check-in before diving into work. Adapts the day's session to Lucy's energy\n3. **Living Story of DataFloat** — Milestone timeline with bookkeeper names, key decisions, momentum tracker for hard days\n\n---\n\n**🛡️ Michael — My picks for what to build FIRST:**\n\n> Priority 1: **Command Shortcuts** — `/standup` and `/risk-check` would save you 10 minutes every morning, zero infrastructure needed\n> Priority 2: **Document Vault** — biggest unlock for DataFlow validation work\n> Priority 3: **Daily Good Morning** — highest emotional ROI, makes the Council feel real\n\nWhich features do you want to build? I can start on any of these today. 🚀"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":601,"cacheRead":169437,"cacheWrite":1786,"totalTokens":171825,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.009015,"cacheRead":0.0508311,"cacheWrite":0.0066975,"total":0.0665466}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772984220891}}
{"type":"message","id":"daed2b9e","parentId":"2898d759","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:38:38.806Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[media attached: /home/openclaw/.openclaw/media/inbound/file_6---c0e9af9f-0c0e-4ac7-99b1-f5831e6f2c50.jpg (image/jpeg) | /home/openclaw/.openclaw/media/inbound/file_6---c0e9af9f-0c0e-4ac7-99b1-f5831e6f2c50.jpg]\nTo send an image back, prefer the message tool (media/path/filePath). If you must inline, use MEDIA:https://example.com/image.jpg (spaces ok, quote if needed) or a safe relative path like MEDIA:./image.jpg. Avoid absolute paths (MEDIA:/...) and ~ paths — they are blocked for security. Keep caption in the text body.\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"89\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 15:38 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nok, first the feature doesn't let me chose a subject, when i pick the round table, I want y'all to discuss about what I'm about to text , and after I stop, I want Michael to put a summary about what did y'all talk about at that round table"},{"type":"image","data":"","mimeType":"image/jpeg"}],"timestamp":1772984318795}}
{"type":"message","id":"da12ed98","parentId":"daed2b9e","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:39:03.030Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy wants two changes to the roundtable:\n\n1. **Choose the subject first** — when she clicks Roundtable, it should use whatever she's typed in the input box as the topic (instead of a default). She wants to type the topic, THEN click Roundtable.\n\n2. **Michael summarizes at the end** — after the roundtable stops (either naturally or via Stop button), Michael should post a summary of what was discussed.\n\nThe current behavior: clicking Roundtable uses the input text OR a default fallback. The issue is it's not clear to the user they should type first. Let me fix the UX:\n- If input is empty, show a prompt asking for the topic\n\n\n- Once the roundtable finishes or gets stopped, I need to trigger Michael to generate and post a summary of the discussion.\n\nI'll update the backend to handle the summary generation and adjust the frontend flow to make it clear the topic needs to come first.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Got it — two clear fixes:\n1. **Type topic first → then click Roundtable** (prompt if empty)\n2. **Michael auto-summarizes** at the end of every roundtable\n\nFixing both now:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_W3JXJrwn4IXI5QwvVOtnn4","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/openclaw/council-room/backend/server.js","old_string":"    } else if (mode === 'roundtable') {\n      // Sequential inter-agent discussion — each agent sees previous responses\n      const agentIds = Object.keys(AGENTS);\n      const topic = message;\n      let transcript = `Lucy's topic: \"${topic}\"\\n\\n`;\n      let stopped = false;\n\n      // Allow client to stop mid-roundtable\n      const stopHandler = (raw) => {\n        try { const d = JSON.parse(raw.toString()); if (d.type === 'stop') stopped = true; } catch {}\n      };\n      socket.on('message', stopHandler);\n\n      for (const id of agentIds) {\n        if (stopped) { send({ type: 'roundtable_stopped', pane: 'council', sessionId }); break; }\n        const prompt = `${transcript}\\nYou are ${AGENTS[id].name} (${AGENTS[id].role}). Respond to the above discussion in 2-4 sentences. Be direct and add your unique perspective. Don't repeat what others said.${memCtx}`;\n        send({ type: 'thinking', agentId: id, agent: AGENTS[id], pane: 'council', sessionId });\n        const response = await runAgent(id, prompt);\n        send({ type: 'response', agentId: id, agent: AGENTS[id], response, pane: 'council', sessionId });\n        transcript += `${AGENTS[id].name}: ${response}\\n\\n`;\n      }\n      socket.off('message', stopHandler);\n      send({ type: 'council_done', pane: 'council', sessionId });","new_string":"    } else if (mode === 'roundtable') {\n      // Sequential inter-agent discussion — each agent sees previous responses\n      const roundtableAgents = ['rafael', 'uriel', 'gabriel', 'raguel']; // Michael summarizes at end\n      const topic = message;\n      let transcript = `Lucy's topic: \"${topic}\"\\n\\n`;\n      let stopped = false;\n\n      const stopHandler = (raw) => {\n        try { const d = JSON.parse(raw.toString()); if (d.type === 'stop') stopped = true; } catch {}\n      };\n      socket.on('message', stopHandler);\n\n      for (const id of roundtableAgents) {\n        if (stopped) break;\n        const prompt = `Council roundtable topic: \"${topic}\"\\n\\nDiscussion so far:\\n${transcript || '(you are first to speak)'}\\n\\nYou are ${AGENTS[id].name} (${AGENTS[id].role}). Add your unique perspective in 2-4 sentences. Build on what others said if applicable. Be direct and specific.${memCtx}`;\n        send({ type: 'thinking', agentId: id, agent: AGENTS[id], pane: 'council', sessionId });\n        const response = await runAgent(id, prompt);\n        send({ type: 'response', agentId: id, agent: AGENTS[id], response, pane: 'council', sessionId });\n        transcript += `${AGENTS[id].name}: ${response}\\n\\n`;\n      }\n      socket.off('message', stopHandler);\n\n      // Michael always summarizes at the end (even if stopped early)\n      send({ type: 'thinking', agentId: 'michael', agent: AGENTS['michael'], pane: 'council', sessionId });\n      const summaryPrompt = `You are Michael, The Wise Advisor. The Council just had a roundtable on: \"${topic}\"\\n\\nHere is the full discussion:\\n${transcript}\\n\\nWrite a concise summary (3-5 sentences) of the key points discussed, any consensus reached, and one clear recommended next action for Lucy. Start with \"📋 Roundtable Summary:\"`;\n      const summary = await runAgent('michael', summaryPrompt);\n      send({ type: 'response', agentId: 'michael', agent: AGENTS['michael'], response: summary, pane: 'council', sessionId });\n      send({ type: 'council_done', pane: 'council', sessionId });"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":1359,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":171819,"totalTokens":173181,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.020385,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.6443212500000001,"total":0.6647152500000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772984318803}}
