{"type":"message","id":"379e23be","parentId":"5592eb0a","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:44:19.507Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Nope — everyone's quiet. 🔇\n\nNo active roundtables, no background conversations. They only talk when triggered — either you message them directly, or a roundtable/council broadcast is running.\n\nRight now it's just you and me. Want to start building those features? 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":78,"cacheRead":174093,"cacheWrite":193,"totalTokens":174365,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.00117,"cacheRead":0.0522279,"cacheWrite":0.00072375,"total":0.05412465}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772984653547}}
{"type":"message","id":"60a75f7c","parentId":"379e23be","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:45:35.923Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"96\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 15:45 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nI didn't turn of the round table , after I switch browser and came back again everyone is quite"}],"timestamp":1772984735906}}
{"type":"message","id":"ac94425b","parentId":"60a75f7c","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:46:18.669Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The roundtable stopped because the WebSocket connection dropped when Lucy switched browsers. The roundtable runs in the backend as an async loop, but the `stopHandler` is attached to the WebSocket connection. When the browser closes/switches, the WebSocket disconnects, which causes the backend to stop processing.\n\nI need to make the roundtable more resilient - it should continue running on the backend even if the client disconnects, and deliver results when they reconnect. Or at minimum, explain why it stopped.\n\nActually the bigger issue is: when the WS closes mid-roundtable, the loop in the backend may have errored out silently. The `send()` calls would fail (socket closed), potentially crashing or silently stopping.\n \nSo I need to decouple the roundtable execution from the WebSocket lifecycle - the backend should keep processing independently and queue results for delivery when the client reconnects.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] That's a WebSocket issue — when you switched browsers, the connection dropped and the roundtable died with it. The backend doesn't keep running when the client disconnects.\n\nFix: make roundtables run as a **background job** on the server — they finish even if you close the browser, then deliver results when you reconnect.\n\nBuilding that now:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_WhlXKCAKZ2XiJNgS5mN3dq","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat > ~/council-room/backend/server.js << 'EOF'\nimport Fastify from 'fastify';\nimport cors from '@fastify/cors';\nimport websocket from '@fastify/websocket';\nimport { spawn } from 'child_process';\nimport { readFileSync, writeFileSync, existsSync } from 'fs';\n\nconst fastify = Fastify({ logger: false });\nawait fastify.register(cors, { origin: true });\nawait fastify.register(websocket);\n\nconst AUTH_TOKEN = process.env.COUNCIL_TOKEN || 'council-88d2f8242c07fcef';\nconst MEMORY_FILE = '/home/openclaw/council-room/memory.json';\nconst EVENTS_FILE = '/home/openclaw/council-room/events.json';\n\nconst AGENTS = {\n  rafael:  { name: 'Rafael',  emoji: '🧭', role: 'The Guide'        },\n  uriel:   { name: 'Uriel',   emoji: '🔥', role: \"God's Fire\"       },\n  michael: { name: 'Michael', emoji: '🛡️', role: 'The Wise Advisor' },\n  gabriel: { name: 'Gabriel', emoji: '📣', role: 'The Voice'        },\n  raguel:  { name: 'Raguel',  emoji: '🤝', role: 'The Friend'       },\n};\n\n// ── PERSISTENT EVENT QUEUE ──\n// Events are saved to disk so reconnecting clients get missed messages\nfunction loadEvents() {\n  try { return JSON.parse(readFileSync(EVENTS_FILE,'utf8')); } catch { return []; }\n}\nfunction appendEvent(ev) {\n  const evs = loadEvents();\n  evs.push({ ...ev, serverTs: Date.now() });\n  if (evs.length > 500) evs.splice(0, evs.length - 500);\n  writeFileSync(EVENTS_FILE, JSON.stringify(evs));\n}\nfunction getEventsSince(ts) {\n  return loadEvents().filter(e => e.serverTs > ts);\n}\n\n// ── MEMORY ──\nfunction loadMemory() {\n  try { return JSON.parse(readFileSync(MEMORY_FILE,'utf8')); } catch { return { facts: [] }; }\n}\nfunction saveMemory(m) { writeFileSync(MEMORY_FILE, JSON.stringify(m,null,2)); }\n\n// ── AGENT RUNNER ──\nfunction runAgent(agentId, message) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const actualId = agentId === 'michael' ? 'main' : agentId;\n    const proc = spawn('openclaw', ['agent','--agent',actualId,'--message',message,'--json'], {\n      env: { ...process.env, HOME: '/home/openclaw' }\n    });\n    let buf = '';\n    proc.stdout.on('data', c => buf += c.toString());\n    proc.on('close', () => {\n      try {\n        const j = JSON.parse(buf);\n        resolve(j?.result?.payloads?.[0]?.text || j?.reply || j?.text || buf.trim());\n      } catch { resolve(buf.trim()); }\n    });\n    proc.on('error', e => resolve(`Error: ${e.message}`));\n  });\n}\n\n// ── CONNECTED CLIENTS ──\nconst clients = new Set();\nfunction broadcast(ev) {\n  appendEvent(ev);\n  clients.forEach(s => { try { if(s.readyState===1) s.send(JSON.stringify(ev)); } catch {} });\n}\n\n// ── ACTIVE ROUNDTABLES ──\nconst activeRoundtables = new Map(); // id -> { stop: fn }\n\n// ── BACKGROUND ROUNDTABLE ──\nasync function runRoundtable(id, topic, sessionId) {\n  let stopped = false;\n  activeRoundtables.set(id, { stop: () => { stopped = true; } });\n\n  const mem = loadMemory();\n  const memCtx = mem.facts.length ? `\\n\\n[Memory: ${mem.facts.map(f=>f.fact).join('; ')}]` : '';\n  const discussants = ['rafael','uriel','gabriel','raguel'];\n  let transcript = '';\n\n  for (const agentId of discussants) {\n    if (stopped) break;\n    broadcast({ type:'thinking', agentId, agent:AGENTS[agentId], pane:'council', sessionId, roundtableId:id });\n    const prompt = `Council roundtable topic: \"${topic}\"\\n\\n${transcript ? 'Discussion so far:\\n'+transcript+'\\n' : ''}You are ${AGENTS[agentId].name} (${AGENTS[agentId].role}). Add your unique perspective in 2-4 sentences. Be direct.${memCtx}`;\n    const response = await runAgent(agentId, prompt);\n    if (stopped && !response) break;\n    broadcast({ type:'response', agentId, agent:AGENTS[agentId], response, pane:'council', sessionId, roundtableId:id });\n    transcript += `${AGENTS[agentId].name}: ${response}\\n\\n`;\n  }\n\n  // Michael always summarizes\n  broadcast({ type:'thinking', agentId:'michael', agent:AGENTS['michael'], pane:'council', sessionId, roundtableId:id });\n  const summaryPrompt = `Council roundtable on: \"${topic}\"\\n\\nDiscussion:\\n${transcript || '(stopped early)'}\\n\\nYou are Michael, The Wise Advisor. Write a concise summary (3-5 sentences): key points, any consensus, and ONE clear next action for Lucy. Start with \"📋 Roundtable Summary:\"${memCtx}`;\n  const summary = await runAgent('michael', summaryPrompt);\n  broadcast({ type:'response', agentId:'michael', agent:AGENTS['michael'], response:summary, pane:'council', sessionId, roundtableId:id });\n  broadcast({ type:'council_done', pane:'council', sessionId, roundtableId:id });\n  activeRoundtables.delete(id);\n}\n\n// ── AUTH ──\nfunction auth(req, reply) {\n  const t = req.headers['x-council-token'] || req.query?.token;\n  if (t !== AUTH_TOKEN) { reply.code(401).send({ error:'Unauthorized' }); return false; }\n  return true;\n}\n\n// ── REST ──\nfastify.get('/health', async (req,reply) => {\n  if(!auth(req,reply))return;\n  return { status:'ok', agents:Object.keys(AGENTS), activeRoundtables:[...activeRoundtables.keys()] };\n});\nfastify.get('/memory', async (req,reply) => { if(!auth(req,reply))return; return loadMemory(); });\nfastify.post('/memory', async (req,reply) => {\n  if(!auth(req,reply))return;\n  const {fact}=req.body; if(!fact) return reply.code(400).send({error:'fact required'});\n  const m=loadMemory(); m.facts.push({fact,ts:Date.now(),date:new Date().toISOString()}); saveMemory(m);\n  return {ok:true,total:m.facts.length};\n});\nfastify.delete('/memory/:idx', async (req,reply) => {\n  if(!auth(req,reply))return;\n  const m=loadMemory(); m.facts.splice(parseInt(req.params.idx),1); saveMemory(m);\n  return {ok:true};\n});\n\n// ── WEBSOCKET ──\nfastify.get('/ws', { websocket:true }, (socket, req) => {\n  const token = new URL(req.url,'http://localhost').searchParams.get('token');\n  const since = parseInt(new URL(req.url,'http://localhost').searchParams.get('since')||'0');\n  if (token !== AUTH_TOKEN) { socket.send(JSON.stringify({type:'error',message:'Unauthorized'})); socket.close(); return; }\n\n  clients.add(socket);\n  socket.send(JSON.stringify({type:'connected'}));\n\n  // Replay missed events since last connection\n  const missed = getEventsSince(since);\n  if (missed.length > 0) {\n    socket.send(JSON.stringify({type:'replay', events:missed}));\n  }\n\n  socket.on('message', async (raw) => {\n    let data; try { data=JSON.parse(raw.toString()); } catch { return; }\n    const {agentId, message, mode, pane, sessionId, type} = data;\n\n    if (type==='stop') {\n      activeRoundtables.forEach(rt => rt.stop());\n      return;\n    }\n    if (!message) return;\n\n    const mem = loadMemory();\n    const memCtx = mem.facts.length ? `\\n\\n[Memory: ${mem.facts.map(f=>f.fact).join('; ')}]` : '';\n\n    if (mode==='roundtable') {\n      const rtId = 'rt_'+Date.now();\n      runRoundtable(rtId, message, sessionId); // fire-and-forget background job\n\n    } else if (mode==='council') {\n      const agentIds = Object.keys(AGENTS);\n      agentIds.forEach(id => broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:id,agent:AGENTS[id],pane:'council',sessionId}));\n      await Promise.all(agentIds.map(async id => {\n        const response = await runAgent(id, message+memCtx);\n        broadcast({type:'response',agentId:id,agent:AGENTS[id],response,pane:'council',sessionId});\n      }));\n      broadcast({type:'council_done',pane:'council',sessionId});\n\n    } else {\n      const targetId = agentId||'rafael';\n      broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:targetId,agent:AGENTS[targetId],pane,sessionId});\n      const response = await runAgent(targetId, message+memCtx);\n      broadcast({type:'response',agentId:targetId,agent:AGENTS[targetId],response,pane,sessionId});\n      broadcast({type:'council_done',pane,sessionId});\n    }\n  });\n\n  socket.on('close', () => clients.delete(socket));\n});\n\nconst PORT = parseInt(process.env.PORT||'3001');\nawait fastify.listen({port:PORT,host:'127.0.0.1'});\nconsole.log(`✅  Council Room API on http://127.0.0.1:${PORT}`);\nconsole.log(`🔑  Token: ${AUTH_TOKEN}`);\nEOF\necho \"Backend written\""}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":2989,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":174378,"totalTokens":177370,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.044835,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.6539175,"total":0.6987615}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772984735918}}
