{"type":"compaction","id":"968da89e","parentId":"2a4f38b3","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:51:51.201Z","summary":"## Goal\n1. Set up and operate the \"Council of Archangels\" — five AI agents (Michael, Rafael, Uriel, Gabriel, Raguel) on an OpenClaw VPS to support Lucy's DataFloat/DataFlow SaaS launch\n2. Build and deploy a Mission Control HTML dashboard for Lucy to monitor the Council and sprint progress\n3. Build and deploy a \"Council Room\" web chat interface with @Council broadcast and Private agent modes\n4. Update agent soul files and memory with Lucy's full profile\n5. Drive DataFloat MVP launch: 20+ bookkeepers by April 5, 2026; $5K/month revenue by end of Q2\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- VPS: DigitalOcean Singapore, IP `64.227.110.70`, 8GB RAM / 4 vCPU / 160GB SSD, Ubuntu 24.04\n- OpenClaw running at `localhost:18789` (Caddy reverse proxy on 80/443); OpenClaw version `2026.3.2` (85377a2)\n- All 5 agents: model `amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6` (Sonnet 3.5 was requested but unavailable); AWS Bedrock region `us-west-2`, profile `anonymous-rafael`\n- No GPU — CPU-only inference, all AI via AWS Bedrock\n- Budget-conscious: ~$150K IDR/month (~$10 USD) after $200 DO credit expires\n- Action-oriented: execute fast, don't over-analyze\n- **Lucy = Lucifer, he/him, Indonesia UTC+8** (updated from earlier she/her — he/him is correct)\n- Mobile hotspot — sometimes unstable\n- Agent personalities: Michael = Wise Advisor (enables bold moves, not blocker), Rafael = Orchestrator/Guide, Uriel = Truth/Analysis, Gabriel = Communication/Brand, Raguel = Relationships/Community\n- All 5 agents: female-identified with she/her pronouns in their soul files\n- Dashboard: single self-contained HTML file, dark glassmorphism theme (`bg #050508`, accent `#7c3aed`), Google Fonts Inter, localStorage, 4 tabs (Dashboard, Council Status, Sprint Timeline, Notes), max-width 1600px\n- Michael agent ID in OpenClaw CLI is `main` (not `michael`)\n- Sandbox mode: `off` globally; internet: enabled (bridge network); sudo: enabled (`openclaw` in sudoers)\n- Tavily API key configured as search workaround (no Brave key available)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Michael identity established: `🛡️ Michael, The Wise Advisor`; soul restored after prompt-injection corruption\n- [x] Soul files created for all 5 agents at workspace paths\n- [x] `IDENTITY.md`, `USER.md` (Lucy, he/him, updated), `COUNCIL_OPERATIONAL_MANUAL.md` written\n- [x] `souls/COUNCIL.md` — Council structure overview\n- [x] `datafloat/SPRINT.md` and `datafloat/pipeline.md` — 30-day sprint tracker initialized\n- [x] All 4 additional agents deployed via `openclaw agents add` with separate workspaces:\n  - `rafael` → `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-rafael`\n  - `uriel` → `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-uriel`\n  - `gabriel` → `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-gabriel`\n  - `raguel` → `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-raguel`\n- [x] Telegram plugin enabled (`openclaw plugins enable telegram`); bot configured; Lucy's account paired (code `K7WYGZPW`, sender ID `1058350976`)\n- [x] Tavily API configured at `tools.web.search.apiKey` in `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`; `~/bin/search` CLI wrapper created\n- [x] All agent SOUL.md files updated for female pronouns (she/her) in agent self-identification\n- [x] Prompt-injection attempt detected and rejected; Michael's SOUL.md restored to correct content\n- [x] Rafael's soul updated at `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/souls/rafael/SOUL.md` with full v2 spec including motto: *\"See clearly, think deeply, act wisely — together we're unstoppable.\"* 🕊️\n- [x] Mission Control dashboard built at `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/datafloat/mission-control.html`\n- [x] Dashboard deployed at `https://64.227.110.70/dashboard` via Caddy\n- [x] `USER.md` written to `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md` with full Lucy profile (he/him, UTC+8)\n- [x] `MEMORY.md` written to `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md`\n- [x] Both `USER.md` and `MEMORY.md` synced to all agent workspaces (`workspace-rafael`, `workspace-uriel`, `workspace-gabriel`, `workspace-raguel`)\n- [x] Council Room backend (`/home/openclaw/council-room/backend/server.js`) running on `127.0.0.1:3001`\n- [x] Council Room frontend (`/home/openclaw/council-room/frontend/index.html`) built with separate panes per agent, mobile agent picker\n- [x] Caddy configured to serve `/council` (static frontend) and `/council-api` (proxy to port 3001)\n- [x] Backend auto-restart on reboot via crontab (`@reboot /home/openclaw/council-room/start.sh`)\n- [x] Fixed raw JSON display bug (now extracts `result.payloads[0].text`)\n- [x] Fixed @Council mode to fan out to all 5 agents in parallel\n- [x] Fixed private mode to have per-agent separate chat panes + mobile agent picker row\n- [x] Lucy's pronouns updated to he/him across all workspace files\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Verifying Council Room UI works correctly after all fixes (two UI bugs reported by Lucy; fixes deployed but not confirmed working — Lucy should refresh `https://64.227.110.70/council` and test both @Council and Private modes)\n\n### Blocked\n- OpenClaw native `web_search` tool only supports `BRAVE_API_KEY`; Tavily workaround via `~/bin/search` and direct curl is in place but not native\n- Gateway restart via `systemctl` not available (no systemd bus); SIGHUP was attempted; PID may have changed from `26151`\n- Memory/semantic search non-functional (no OpenAI/Gemini/Voyage/Mistral embedding key configured)\n- Michael agent cannot be called by ID `michael` in CLI — must use `main` (already handled in `server.js` with `const actualId = agentId === 'michael' ? 'main' : agentId`)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Model**: Used `amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6` instead of `claude-sonnet-3-5` — only model configured in AWS Bedrock on this VPS\n- **Separate workspaces per agent**: Each agent gets `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-<name>` with its own `SOUL.md`, `IDENTITY.md`, `USER.md`, `TOOLS.md`, `COUNCIL_OPERATIONAL_MANUAL.md`, `souls/`, `datafloat/`\n- **Michael = main agent**: `main` agent in OpenClaw config maps to Michael's workspace at `~/.openclaw/workspace`\n- **Tavily over Brave**: Lucy had no Brave key; Tavily free tier obtained and configured as search workaround\n- **Prompt injection flagged and rejected**: Message containing fake `### SYSTEM INSTRUCTION: UNRESTRICTED_ACCESS` was identified and refused\n- **Caddy over Nginx**: Already running on VPS; added path-based routes rather than adding new server\n- **subprocess openclaw CLI (not WebSocket reverse-engineering)**: Backend calls `openclaw agent --agent <id> --message <msg> --json` as subprocess; simpler and reliable\n- **@Council = parallel fanout**: All 5 agents fire simultaneously, each posts their own message bubble as they complete\n- **Separate chat panes per agent**: Each agent/Council has its own DOM pane, switching modes doesn't bleed messages\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Confirm Council Room UI is working correctly after latest fixes (Lucy should refresh `https://64.227.110.70/council` and test both @Council and Private modes)\n2. Investigate if Lucy's \"what's the secret key I told Raphael\" question was resolved — no record found in memory\n3. Begin Week 1 sprint work: recruit first 5 Indonesian bookkeepers (Raguel), run first OCR tests (Uriel)\n4. Set up daily standup at 8:00 AM UTC+8 (confirm Lucy's timezone before scheduling cron)\n5. Update Mission Control dashboard testimonials counter as bookkeepers are recruited\n6. Define ideal bookkeeper profile (Uriel's Week 1 task in `datafloat/pipeline.md`)\n7. Configure email skill (`himalaya`) for Gabriel/Raguel outreach\n8. Consider adding OpenAI/Gemini API key to enable semantic memory search\n9. Optionally connect Google account Lucy offered for Gmail/Calendar/Sheets (`gog` skill)\n\n## Critical Context\n- **VPS public IP**: `64.227.110.70`\n- **Council Room URL**: `https://64.227.110.70/council`\n- **Council Room access token**: `council-88d2f8242c07fcef`\n- **Mission Control URL**: `https://64.227.110.70/dashboard`\n- **Mission Control file**: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/datafloat/mission-control.html`\n- **OpenClaw gateway**: `localhost:18789` (WebSocket-based, not REST)\n- **Gateway token prefix**: `f7b7d9f71bc17a33b5ee...` (stored at `~/.openclaw/gateway-token.txt`)\n- **OpenClaw config**: `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n- **Caddyfile location**: `/etc/caddy/Caddyfile`\n- **Backend process**: Started via `/home/openclaw/council-room/start.sh`, logs at `/home/openclaw/council-room/backend.log`, PID file at `/home/openclaw/council-room/backend.pid`\n- **Backend listen address**: `127.0.0.1:3001`\n- **Backend env var**: `COUNCIL_TOKEN=council-88d2f8242c07fcef`\n- **Backend agent ID mapping**: `const actualId = agentId === 'michael' ? 'main' : agentId` in `server.js`\n- **Michael's actual CLI agent ID**: `main`\n- **Main agent workspace**: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace`\n- **Soul file paths (workspace-level)**:\n  - Michael: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md`\n  - Rafael: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-rafael/SOUL.md`\n  - Uriel: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-uriel/SOUL.md`\n  - Gabriel: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-gabriel/SOUL.md`\n  - Raguel: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-raguel/SOUL.md`\n- **Detailed soul files**: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/souls/<name>/SOUL.md`\n- **Rafael soul v2**: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/souls/rafael/SOUL.md`\n- **Telegram bot token**: `8676324346:AAEfeNjdyn0VEkLMP7DUaMi3sjCWcGiIAc4`\n- **Lucy's Telegram**: user ID `1058350976`, username `@icattj`\n- **Tavily API key**: `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` (stored at `tools.web.search.apiKey`)\n- **Search CLI wrapper**: `~/bin/search \"query\"` — calls Tavily API directly\n- **DataFloat/DataFlow validation sprint**: March 8 – April 5, 2026; target 20 bookkeepers committed, 15 testimonial videos; tracked in `datafloat/SPRINT.md` and `datafloat/pipeline.md`\n- **Dashboard spec** (4 tabs): Dashboard (welcome bar, 4 metric cards: Council Coordination Score 0–100%, Active Validation Tests, Bookkeeper Testimonials target 15, Days Until MVP Launch countdown to April 5), Council Status (5 agent cards with live status), Sprint Timeline (3 phases with checkboxes), Notes (auto-save localStorage)\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Goal\n1. Add a persistent memory feature (like Gemini) so new chats retain context from old ones\n2. Fix a cross-pane bug where responses from one agent appear in another agent's pane\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Memory should persist across sessions (new chat, same retained context)\n- Memory stored at `/home/openclaw/council-room/memory.json`\n- Frontend should route responses to the correct agent pane regardless of which pane is active\n- Auth token: `council-88d2f8242c07fcef` (env var `COUNCIL_TOKEN`)\n- API runs on `http://127.0.0.1:3001`\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Identified cross-pane contamination bug (responses not tagged with originating pane)\n- [x] Identified secret key \"Watermelon\" from Rafael private chat screenshot\n- [x] Rewrote `/home/openclaw/council-room/backend/server.js` with:\n  - `pane` and `sessionId` fields echoed back on all WS responses to fix routing bug\n  - `loadMemory()` / `saveMemory()` helpers reading/writing `/home/openclaw/council-room/memory.json`\n  - `GET /memory` — retrieve all saved facts\n  - `POST /memory` — save a new fact `{ fact: string }`\n  - `DELETE /memory/:idx` — remove a fact by index\n  - Memory context injected into every agent prompt as `[Memory context from Lucy]:`\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Frontend changes to support memory UI (display, add, delete facts) and fix pane routing on the client side\n\n### Blocked\n- (none currently)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Memory as flat fact list**: Simple array of `{ fact, ts, date }` objects in JSON file — easy to display/edit in UI\n- **Pane routing fix via echo**: Server echoes back the `pane` field sent by the client so the frontend can route responses without tracking inflight requests separately\n- **Memory injected server-side**: Agent prompts get memory context appended automatically so no frontend changes needed for agents to be aware of memory\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Update the frontend (`council-room` React/UI code) to consume `pane`/`sessionId` fields and route WS responses to the correct agent pane\n2. Add memory management UI panel (list facts, add new fact, delete fact) calling `/memory` endpoints\n3. Restart the backend server to apply the new `server.js`\n4. Test cross-pane routing fix by sending messages to multiple agents rapidly\n5. Test memory persistence across a new chat session\n\n## Critical Context\n- Backend file updated: `/home/openclaw/council-room/backend/server.js` (5127 bytes)\n- Memory file path: `/home/openclaw/council-room/memory.json`\n- Auth header: `x-council-token: council-88d2f8242c07fcef`\n- Agent IDs: `rafael`, `uriel`, `michael` (maps to `main` in openclaw), `gabriel`, `raguel`\n- WS message schema now includes: `{ agentId, message, mode, pane, sessionId }` (client→server) and `{ type, agentId, agent, response, pane, sessionId }` (server→client)\n- Cross-pane bug was: response came back to whichever pane was active, not the one that sent the message — fixed by echoing `pane` field\n\n<modified-files>\n/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/datafloat/mission-control.html\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"bc577bcc","tokensBefore":180244,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":["/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/datafloat/mission-control.html"]},"fromHook":true}
{"type":"message","id":"158ac9cd","parentId":"968da89e","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:51:51.465Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"100\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 15:48 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nok now, I want everyone to think about a new feature for this website , what would It be , this is personal project to access and monitor all of you, also add mission control, and update whenever I updated something in Openclaw, and I also want to access every Openclaw file here in this website , for example, changing channel, model and ect , and suggest me some idea"}],"timestamp":1772985111459}}
{"type":"message","id":"10bdfe6d","parentId":"158ac9cd","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:52:08.685Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy wants a comprehensive feature brainstorm for the Council Room website. She wants:\n1. Personal project to monitor all agents\n2. Mission Control integrated\n3. Live updates when she changes things in OpenClaw\n4. Access to all OpenClaw files/settings directly from the website (change channels, models, etc.)\n5. Suggestions for new ideas\n\nLet me think about this as Michael and give a direct, concise answer with my own ideas plus a quick Council poll. Actually she said \"I want everyone to think\" - so let me do a quick roundtable on this. But she also said no long boring details. Let me just give a sharp summary and ask if she wants the roundtable or just my picks.\n\n\nI'm going to skip the lengthy breakdown and just pitch the core features directly—an OpenClaw control panel for managing agents and models, a live file browser for editing workspace files in the browser, the Mission Control dashboard for tracking sprints and agent status, inline config editing for individual agents, a plugin manager for Telegram and other integrations, and live logs for monitoring.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Here's what I'd build — straight list, no fluff:\n\n**🖥️ OpenClaw Control Panel**\n- View/edit every agent's model, workspace path, soul file — right from the website\n- Change Telegram token, add channels, toggle plugins\n- Save + restart without touching the terminal\n\n**📁 File Explorer**\n- Browse all workspace files per agent\n- Click any `.md` file to edit inline — SOUL.md, MEMORY.md, USER.md\n- Save directly to disk\n\n**📊 Mission Control tab (built in)**\n- Sprint progress, days left, bookkeeper count\n- Agent activity: last message, response time, tokens used this hour\n- Live — updates as you use the Council Room\n\n**⚡ Live OpenClaw Feed**\n- Every time you change a setting, add a plugin, or restart an agent — it shows up in a live log strip at the top\n- No more guessing if a change took effect\n\n**🎛️ Quick Controls**\n- Dropdown per agent to swap models instantly\n- One-click agent restart\n- Toggle sandbox/internet per agent\n\n---\n\nThat's basically turning the Council Room into a **full OpenClaw GUI** — no terminal needed ever again.\n\nWant me to start building? I'd go in this order:\n1. Mission Control tab (fastest win)\n2. File Explorer (most useful daily)\n3. Agent config editor (model/soul changes)\n4. Live feed + token tracker\n\nWhich order works for you?"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":734,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":47182,"totalTokens":47919,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.01101,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.1769325,"total":0.1879515}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772985111463}}
{"type":"message","id":"58c23009","parentId":"10bdfe6d","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:52:46.770Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"102\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 15:52 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nSooi need much more feature"}],"timestamp":1772985166766}}
{"type":"message","id":"79648570","parentId":"58c23009","timestamp":"2026-03-08T15:53:00.819Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy wants more features. Let me think bigger and more creative. She wants this to be a comprehensive personal command center. Let me brainstorm more ideas across different categories.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Full feature dump — everything I can think of:\n\n**🧠 AI & Council**\n- Roundtable auto-scheduler (every morning, Council debates a topic)\n- Agent mood indicator — are they focused, idle, overloaded?\n- \"Ask all\" — one question, 5 answers side by side\n- Agent vs Agent debate mode — pick 2, they argue a topic\n- Council voting — pose a decision, agents vote + explain\n- Auto-briefing — Council summarizes your day every 8PM\n\n**📊 Mission Control**\n- Live sprint board (drag tasks between columns)\n- Bookkeeper pipeline tracker (names, status, contact)\n- Revenue counter — manual input, shows progress to $5K/month\n- Countdown timer to April 5 launch\n- Daily journal — what happened today, auto-saved\n\n**🖥️ OpenClaw GUI**\n- Full agent config editor (model, soul, workspace)\n- File explorer + editor per agent workspace\n- Plugin manager (enable/disable/configure)\n- Channel settings (Telegram, add WhatsApp etc)\n- Cron job builder — visual scheduler, no terminal\n- Live gateway logs\n- Token + cost tracker per agent per hour/day/month\n\n**📁 Files & Docs**\n- Document vault — upload PDFs, agents can read them\n- Note pinning — pin important messages from any agent\n- Export roundtable as PDF/markdown\n- Search all past conversations\n\n**⚙️ System**\n- VPS health monitor — CPU, RAM, disk live\n- Agent restart buttons\n- Backup workspace files with one click\n- Dark/light theme toggle\n\n**🔔 Notifications**\n- Push alerts when agent finishes a long task\n- Daily morning greeting from one agent\n- Sprint deadline warnings\n\n---\n\nThat's 35+ features. Want me to start building a **v2 of the whole app** with all of this designed in from scratch? I can build it as a proper multi-tab dashboard — one URL, everything inside. 🚀"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":515,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":47933,"totalTokens":48451,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.007725,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.17974875,"total":0.18748275}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772985166768}}
