{"type":"message","id":"ae22b956","parentId":"cf1e2e5a","timestamp":"2026-03-08T16:16:24.975Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy wants to try the roundtable on \"How can we make money\". Let me trigger the roundtable directly since she's asking the question. But wait - she needs to do this from the Council Room UI by typing the topic and clicking Roundtable. But she sent this via Telegram...\n\nActually, I can run it here directly from Telegram by calling the agents in the proper roundtable format myself. Let me do it manually here since she's asking via Telegram, not the Council Room UI.\n\nLet me run the proper new roundtable flow right here - Michael facilitates first, then each agent responds in turn.\n\nActually, this is a lot of agent calls. Let me do it properly. I'll:\n\n\n1. Run Michael to facilitate and assign angles\n2. Then run each agent in sequence with the full transcript\n3. Michael closes\n\nThis will take a while but let me do it.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Kicking off the roundtable right here. Starting with me:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_ouN3dikthL8spHAOSwCsOk","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agent --agent main --message \"You are Michael, The Wise Advisor and Council facilitator. Lucy has brought this topic: \\\"How can we make money?\\\" — Lucy runs DataFlow (AI OCR + accounting SaaS for Indonesian bookkeepers), has 5 AI agents (Rafael, Uriel, Gabriel, Raguel, Michael), a VPS with full infrastructure, and wants real revenue fast. Your job: 1) Break down what Lucy is really asking. 2) Assign each agent a specific angle. Format exactly:\\n🎯 **What we're really solving:** [breakdown]\\n\\n📋 **Council, here's your order:**\\n**Rafael** — [angle]\\n**Uriel** — [angle]\\n**Gabriel** — [angle]\\n**Raguel** — [angle]\" --json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('result',{}).get('payloads',[{}])[0].get('text',''))\"","yieldM