{"type":"message","id":"89294ed4","parentId":"d581a850","timestamp":"2026-03-08T17:49:50.098Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is emphatic - no more fake/dummy data. Everything needs to be REAL. This means:\n- Agent health checks must actually ping the agents\n- Token tracking must be real (not estimated)\n- Agent monitoring must show actual live status\n- No dummy UI elements showing fake data\n- Everything that looks like it's tracking something must actually be tracking it\n\nShe's right - the current system has a lot of UI elements that look functional but are just showing placeholder/estimated data. She wants real, working monitoring.\n\nI need to:\n1. Build real agent health checks (actually call each agent, measure response time)\n2. Real token tracking (count actual tokens from responses)\n3. Real model configuration changes\n4. Real agent restart capability\n5. Real live data only - no estimates, no placeholders\n\nLet me acknowledge this and commit to building only real, functional monitoring.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Agreed.** No more dummy data. Everything in the app will be:\n- ✅ Real agent health (actually ping, measure response time)\n- ✅ Real token counts (count actual tokens from responses)\n- ✅ Real model switching (actual config changes, real restarts)\n- ✅ Real uptime tracking (no fake status badges)\n\nIf it can't be real, it won't be in the UI. Period.\n\nBuilding now. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":310,"cacheRead":90494,"cacheWrite":370,"totalTokens":91184,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0015500000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0090494,"cacheWrite":0.0004625,"total":0.0110719}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772992185494}}
