{"type":"message","id":"b3aa3cd4","parentId":"c152f9f3","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:03:42.141Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking if the agent monitoring system fixes are done. I was supposed to be building real agent health checks, real token tracking, and smart model switching. I said \"Building now\" and she's checking back 14 minutes later.\n\nI haven't actually written the code yet. I got caught up in the conversation and didn't implement it. Let me be honest - I need to actually build this now. Let me:\n\n1. Add real agent health check endpoints\n2. Add actual token tracking (not estimated)\n3. Add smart agent restart (individual agent, not whole backend)\n4. Update the frontend to show real status\n\nLet me do this properly now.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"No — still building. Let me finish it now:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_wGryohkO54P87qIMYdaDS3","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/openclaw/council-room/backend/server.js","oldText":"// ── openclaw agents list ──\nfastify.get('/oc/agents', async(req,rep)=>{\n  if(!auth(req,rep))return;\n  try{ const r=execSync('openclaw agents list --json 2>/dev/null').toString(); return {agents:JSON.parse(r)}; }\n  catch{ return {agents:Object.keys(AGENTS).map(id=>({id,name:AGENTS[id].name}))}; }\n});","newString":"// ── openclaw agents list + REAL health check ──\nfastify.get('/oc/agents', async(req,rep)=>{\n  if(!auth(req,rep))return;\n  const health = {};\n  for(const id of Object.keys(AGENTS)){\n    const start = Date.now();\n    try{\n      const res = await runAgent(id, 'Respond with one word: OK');\n      const latency = Date.now() - start;\n      health[id] = { status: 'up', latency, lastSeen: Date.now() };\n    }catch(e){\n      health[id] = { status: 'down', error: e.message, lastSeen: Date.now() };\n    }\n  }\n  return {agents:Object.keys(AGENTS).map(id=>({id,name:AGENTS[id].name,...health[id]}))};\n});\n\n// ── agent restart (individual, not full backend) ──\nfastify.post('/oc/agent/:id/restart', async(req,rep)=>{\n  if(!auth(req,rep))return;\n  const id=req.params.id;\n  const aid = id==='michael'?'main':id;\n  try{\n    // Try to gracefully restart via openclaw CLI\n    execSync(`openclaw agent --agent ${aid} --message 'System restart initiated' 2>/dev/null`, {timeout:5000}).toString();\n    return {ok:true,message:`${AGENTS[id]?.name||id} restarted`,timestamp:Date.now()};\n  }catch(e){\n    return rep.code(500).send({error:e.message});\n  }\n});\n\n// ── model config per agent ──\nfastify.get('/oc/agent/:id/config', async(req,rep)=>{\n  if(!auth(req,rep))return;\n  const id=req.params.id;\n  try{\n    const cfg = jread(OC_CONFIG,{});\n    return {agentId:id,currentModel:cfg.agents?.[id]?.model||'amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6'};\n  }catch{return rep.code(500).send({error:'Failed to read config'});}\n});\n\nfastify.post('/oc/agent/:id/model', async(req,rep)=>{\n  if(!auth(req,rep))return;\n  const id=req.params.id;\n  const {model}=req.body;\n  if(!model)return rep.code(400).send({error:'model required'});\n  try{\n    const cfg = jread(OC_CONFIG,{});\n    if(!cfg.agents)cfg.agents={};\n    if(!cfg.agents[id])cfg.agents[id]={};\n    cfg.agents[id].model=model;\n    jwrite(OC_CONFIG,cfg);\n    // Restart the agent to pick up new model\n    const aid = id==='michael'?'main':id;\n    try{execSync(`pkill -f \"openclaw agent.*${aid}\" 2>/dev/null`);}catch{}\n    return {ok:true,message:`${AGENTS[id]?.name||id} model updated to ${model.split('/').pop()}, restarting...`,timestamp:Date.now()};\n  }catch(e){return rep.code(500).send({error:e.message});}\n});"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":1205,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":91121,"totalTokens":92336,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.006025000000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.11390125000000001,"total":0.11993625000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772993012175}}
