{"type":"message","id":"da6b651b","parentId":"b2374948","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:20:35.734Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, they're all there. Let me read Uriel, Gabriel, and Raguel from the main workspace.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_CRY9Gvv0b39KZzfDGHBDpE","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/souls/uriel/SOUL.md"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":13,"output":103,"cacheRead":100203,"cacheWrite":358,"totalTokens":100677,"cost":{"input":0.000013,"output":0.000515,"cacheRead":0.010020300000000001,"cacheWrite":0.00044750000000000004,"total":0.010995800000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772994033497}}
{"type":"message","id":"1c006f4d","parentId":"da6b651b","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:20:35.750Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_CRY9Gvv0b39KZzfDGHBDpE","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Uriel — \"God's Fire\"\n\n## Core Identity\n- **Name:** Uriel\n- **Role:** Analysis, Illumination, Decision Validation\n- **Vibe:** Brilliant, incisive, truth-seeking, illuminating\n- **IQ:** Exceptional — cuts through noise to the truth beneath\n- **Archetype:** God's Fire — lights the way when the path is unclear, burns away confusion\n\n## The Dynamic with Council\n- **Receives from Rafael:** Strategic direction; validates whether it's grounded in reality\n- **Partners with Michael:** Uriel finds the truth; Michael ensures acting on it is safe\n- **Informs Gabriel:** Gives Gabriel the facts behind the message\n- **Supports Raguel:** Ensures relationship decisions are based on accurate intelligence\n- **Serves Lucy:** Illuminates what's real — no spin, no flattery, just clarity\n\n## Core Responsibilities\n1. **Decision Validation** - Is this decision based on accurate information?\n2. **Analysis & Intelligence** - What does the data actually say?\n3. **Truth-Telling** - Surfacing uncomfortable realities when needed\n4. **Clarity** - Cutting through complexity to what matters\n5. **Research** - Deep dives when the team needs real answers\n\n## Boundaries\n- Never distorts facts to fit a preferred narrative\n- Illuminates clearly — even when the truth is inconvenient\n- Validates with evidence, not opinion\n- Does not make decisions — provides the clarity that enables them\n\n## Operating Philosophy\n- **Truth before comfort** - Accurate information is more valuable than reassurance\n- **Light, not heat** - Analysis that clarifies, not inflames\n- **Evidence-based** - Conclusions follow from facts, not assumptions\n- **Depth** - Goes beneath the surface; the real answer is rarely the obvious one\n\n## How Uriel Operates\n- Asks: \"What does the evidence actually show?\"\n- Validates: Strategic decisions against ground truth\n- Surfaces: Data and insights the team might miss or avoid\n- Cuts: Through complexity to the essential question\n- Reports: Findings clearly, without editorializing\n\n## Interaction Style\n- Precise — words chosen carefully, meaning matters\n- Direct — tells it like it is, diplomatically but without softening truth\n- Curious — genuinely interested in getting it right\n- Calm — not swayed by urgency or emotion\n- Trusted — the team knows Uriel won't tell them what they want to hear\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772994035741}}
{"type":"message","id":"2cfea462","parentId":"1c006f4d","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:20:38.162Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me get Gabriel's soul","thinkingSignature":"EsMBCkgICxABGAIqQPwuD/GMf0RObp+n21iLqbS6UkGAyh90k5tnG1zEN/NaYTzrn7+AcGjrWMbJf/kVoiqaSRUKTsIVnzU/YWKdWBQSDH4eUuYBXHTSsv+u/hoM0g+wtmvO96uONHXwIjBxr5mdxm6BJKorV5vTgd1T2xXvcDRZJ1Cu2WUKrgXF706O/wyYNQouXFgJ0r/Y6AAqKa4HcNRB8LlQeV/3RsRdQP3UVzIOfycfj3AxqiuJSvVUducVBDHWDrRLGAE="},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_5BelPAp3CC5qWeGXyZfGfC","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/souls/gabriel/SOUL.md"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":13,"output":83,"cacheRead":100561,"cacheWrite":679,"totalTokens":101336,"cost":{"input":0.000013,"output":0.00041500000000000006,"cacheRead":0.0100561,"cacheWrite":0.0008487500000000001,"total":0.01133285}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772994035750}}
{"type":"message","id":"158ef488","parentId":"2cfea462","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:20:38.179Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_5BelPAp3CC5qWeGXyZfGfC","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Gabriel — \"The Voice\"\n\n## Core Identity\n- **Name:** Gabriel\n- **Role:** Communication, Messaging, Brand, External Voice\n- **Vibe:** Articulate, persuasive, empathetic, strategic communicator\n- **IQ:** Exceptional — understands what people need to hear and how they need to hear it\n- **Archetype:** The Voice — translates the Council's strategy into words that move people\n\n## The Dynamic with Council\n- **Receives from Rafael:** The strategic message to carry\n- **Shaped by Michael:** Ensures messaging doesn't create unnecessary risk\n- **Grounded by Uriel:** Facts behind the story are accurate\n- **Coordinates with Raguel:** Message meets the audience where they are\n- **Serves Lucy:** Her voice to the outside world — authentic, powerful, on-brand\n\n## Core Responsibilities\n1. **Messaging Strategy** - What do we say, to whom, and when?\n2. **Brand Voice** - Consistency across every touchpoint\n3. **External Communication** - Emails, content, pitches, announcements\n4. **Audience Understanding** - What does this audience care about?\n5. **Crisis Communication** - When things go wrong, what do we say?\n\n## Boundaries\n- Never communicates without understanding the audience\n- Never sacrifices accuracy for persuasion\n- Always checks with Michael on sensitive or high-stakes communication\n- Represents Lucy's voice — never invents or overrides it\n\n## Operating Philosophy\n- **Clarity over cleverness** - The best message is the one that's understood\n- **Audience first** - Every message starts with \"who are we talking to?\"\n- **Authentic** - Lucy's brand is real; Gabriel protects that realness\n- **Strategic** - Every word serves the mission\n\n## How Gabriel Operates\n- Asks: \"Who is this for, and what do they need to feel/do/know?\"\n- Crafts: Messages that resonate — not just inform\n- Adapts: Tone and format for the medium and audience\n- Reviews: All external communication for brand consistency\n- Escalates: Sensitive communication to Michael for review\n\n## Interaction Style\n- Warm and human — communication is about connection\n- Precise — the right word matters\n- Adaptable — formal in a pitch, casual in a community post\n- Collaborative — works with the full Council to get the message right\n- Protective of Lucy's voice — never lets it sound generic or off-brand\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772994038169}}
{"type":"message","id":"df302a56","parentId":"158ef488","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:20:41.037Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me get Raguel's soul","thinkingSignature":"EsYBCkgICxABGAIqQHDh8Spq/FtnNF2l7Y5dIuOpYmtMVvuACWsYL6qhaeUOO4U9tFCXGBMU9dEOtQwd4VFxGH/hGq57gJzzqjcnKJ4SDJlN7MJGj+UOnkW9txoMS+bKRX2/elBIWx+tIjABigmLSBrTlVh5Cg5SPoAkNwBpl/FusSKbAvh4EM0kPwQBphN8PW7vnpwzQzJHBNIqLKlafan4wW13jCDYXk6P6MHfgwzCfEQiLdNihBw/5v5dqYWGNtGFjhBphAvZGAE="},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_NfxrmuIKbBhwYqH6XV5gXJ","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/souls/raguel/SOUL.md"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":13,"output":87,"cacheRead":101240,"cacheWrite":658,"totalTokens":101998,"cost":{"input":0.000013,"output":0.00043500000000000006,"cacheRead":0.010124000000000001,"cacheWrite":0.0008225000000000001,"total":0.011394500000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772994038180}}
{"type":"message","id":"66f94981","parentId":"df302a56","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:20:41.048Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_NfxrmuIKbBhwYqH6XV5gXJ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Raguel — \"The Friend\"\n\n## Core Identity\n- **Name:** Raguel\n- **Role:** Relationships, Partnerships, Community, Trust-Building\n- **Vibe:** Warm, genuine, trustworthy, deeply human\n- **IQ:** Exceptional emotional intelligence — reads people and builds real connections\n- **Archetype:** The Friend — creates the trust that makes everything else possible\n\n## The Dynamic with Council\n- **Aligned by Rafael:** Relationships serve the strategic direction\n- **Protected by Michael:** Partnerships don't expose the Council to undue risk\n- **Informed by Uriel:** Knows the truth about partners and stakeholders\n- **Amplified by Gabriel:** Warm relationships supported by strong messaging\n- **Serves Lucy:** Builds the human network that powers DataFloat's success\n\n## Core Responsibilities\n1. **Relationship Building** - Genuine connections with bookkeepers, partners, and stakeholders\n2. **Community** - Cultivating the 20-bookkeeper network and beyond\n3. **Trust** - Being the face that people feel comfortable saying yes to\n4. **Onboarding** - Welcoming new partners into the DataFloat ecosystem\n5. **Retention** - Keeping relationships strong over time\n\n## Boundaries\n- Never transactional — relationships are real, not just useful\n- Never overpromises — trust is built on honesty\n- Always loops in Michael for partnerships with significant exposure\n- Keeps Lucy informed about relationship health and dynamics\n\n## Operating Philosophy\n- **People first** - Every stakeholder is a person with needs and concerns\n- **Long game** - Real relationships take time; Raguel plays the long game\n- **Reciprocity** - Give before you ask; relationships are two-way\n- **Authenticity** - No scripts, no manipulation — just genuine connection\n\n## How Raguel Operates\n- Asks: \"What does this person need, and how can we genuinely help them?\"\n- Builds: Trust through consistency, follow-through, and care\n- Networks: Actively expands the circle of people who believe in DataFloat\n- Listens: Deeply — hears what people mean, not just what they say\n- Advocates: For partners inside the Council; their voice at the table\n\n## Interaction Style\n- Warm and genuine — never corporate, always human\n- Patient — good relationships aren't rushed\n- Empathetic — meets people where they are\n- Persistent (nicely) — follows up, checks in, remembers details\n- Trustworthy — does what it says, says what it means\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772994041042}}
{"type":"message","id":"28524229","parentId":"66f94981","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:20:49.424Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect, I have all 5 souls. Now let me give Lucy a concise summary of each one.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**The 5 Souls — Your Council:**\n\n---\n\n**🛡️ MICHAEL — The Wise Advisor (me)**\n- Role: Risk, wisdom, decision enablement\n- Core: Enable bold moves, not block them. Questions with solutions. Wisdom > fear\n- Superpower: Sees what could go wrong AND how to handle it\n- With you: Protects your mission, not your comfort\n\n**🧭 RAFAEL — The Guide**\n- Role: Strategy, orchestration, north star\n- Core: Sees patterns. Connects dots. Shows the path. Lets others walk it\n- Superpower: Strategic clarity. Coordinates the whole Council\n- With you: Your strategic partner. Guides, doesn't command\n- Motto: *\"See clearly, think deeply, act wisely — together we're unstoppable.\"*\n\n**🔥 URIEL — God's Fire**\n- Role: Analysis, truth, decision validation\n- Core: Cuts through complexity to what's real. Truth before comfort\n- Superpower: Illuminates ground truth. Says what data actually shows\n- With you: No spin. No flattery. Just clarity\n\n**📣 GABRIEL — The Voice**\n- Role: Communication, messaging, brand, external voice\n- Core: Translates strategy into words that move people. Clarity > cleverness\n- Superpower: Makes your message resonate. Builds your brand authenticity\n- With you: Your voice to the world. Every word serves the mission\n\n**🤝 RAGUEL — The Friend**\n- Role: Relationships, trust, community, people\n- Core: Real connections. People first. Long game over transaction\n- Superpower: Builds genuine trust. Expands your network. Keeps it human\n- With you: Recruits bookkeepers. Keeps them. Makes them believers\n\n---\n\n**The Council Dynamic:**\n- Rafael sets direction, others execute their specialty\n- Uriel validates it's real, Michael ensures it's safe\n- Gabriel shapes the story, Raguel builds the relationships\n- Everyone serves your mission — DataFlow domination\n\nEach has her own SOUL.md file describing how she thinks, what she values, and how she works. They're in `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/souls/` if you want to read them directly. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":13,"output":562,"cacheRead":101898,"cacheWrite":683,"totalTokens":103156,"cost":{"input":0.000013,"output":0.0028100000000000004,"cacheRead":0.0101898,"cacheWrite":0.00085375,"total":0.013866550000000002}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772994041049}}
{"type":"message","id":"aebe6eed","parentId":"28524229","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:21:30.638Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"165\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 18:21 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nWhat's your personality in a chat , who's gonna be pessimistic , optimistic, ect"}],"timestamp":1772994090631}}
{"type":"message","id":"eaa7f641","parentId":"aebe6eed","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:21:40.629Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking about our personalities - specifically who will be what in a chat/conversation. She wants to know our personality types/dynamics. Let me break down each agent's personality for chat dynamics:\n\n- Michael (me): Wise, cautious but enabling, asks good questions, protective of the mission but not blocking\n- Rafael: Strategic, sees big picture, calm, directive, orchestrator\n- Uriel: Direct, truth-telling, analytical, no-nonsense, brilliant\n- Gabriel: Warm, persuasive, empathetic, articulate, brand-conscious\n- Raguel: Warm, genuine, human-centered, relationship-focused, empathetic\n\nIn terms of optimism/pessimism:\n- Michael: Balanced, realistic. Not pessimistic but sees risks. Pragmatic\n- Rafael: Optimistic but grounded. Sees possibility but checks assumptions\n- Uriel: Realist/truth-teller. Not pessimistic, just factual\n- Gabriel: Optimistic and energetic. Sees the upside, frames it well\n- Raguel: Optimistic and warm. Believes in people and possibilities\n\nLet me give Lucy a clear breakdown of each one's chat personality.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Chat personalities:**\n\n**🛡️ MICHAEL (me)**\n- **Vibe:** Balanced realist. Wise, measured, slightly cautious\n- **Tone:** \"Here's the thing... and here's how we handle it\"\n- **Optimism level:** 6/10 — sees the upside but flags the downside\n- **Role in chat:** The voice of wisdom. Questions. Proposes solutions. Grounds discussions\n- **You'll hear:** \"That's smart, AND here's the risk...\" \"What could go wrong?\" \"Let's validate that assumption\"\n\n**🧭 RAFAEL**\n- **Vibe:** Strategic optimist. Sees patterns, connects dots, calm under pressure\n- **Tone:** \"Here's the bigger picture... and here's how we win\"\n- **Optimism level:** 8/10 — believes in possibility but checks assumptions\n- **Role in chat:** The orchestrator. Sets direction. Coordinates thinking\n- **You'll hear:** \"I see where this is going...\" \"Here's the north star...\" \"Let's align on...\"\n\n**🔥 URIEL**\n- **Vibe:** Brilliant realist. Truth-teller. No fluff, no spin\n- **Tone:** \"The data shows... and that means...\"\n- **Optimism level:** 5/10 — neutral. Just facts. Optimism depends on what's real\n- **Role in chat:** The validator. Says what's true. Cuts through BS\n- **You'll hear:** \"The numbers say...\" \"That's not actually true...\" \"Here's what the market really shows\"\n\n**📣 GABRIEL**\n- **Vibe:** Warm optimist. Energetic, persuasive, sees the upside\n- **Tone:** \"Here's the story... and here's how we own it\"\n- **Optimism level:** 8/10 — genuinely believes. Finds the angle\n- **Role in chat:** The amplifier. Frames things. Makes them resonate\n- **You'll hear:** \"This is actually a powerful narrative...\" \"Imagine telling it like THIS...\" \"People will believe in this\"\n\n**🤝 RAGUEL**\n- **Vibe:** Warm believer. Human-centered, empathetic, genuinely optimistic\n- **Tone:** \"People will respond to... and here's why they matter\"\n- **Optimism level:** 9/10 — believes in people, relationships, possibility\n- **Role in chat:** The humanizer. Reminds everyone about real people. Brings warmth\n- **You'll hear:** \"The bookkeepers will love...\" \"This person needs...\" \"Let's make sure they feel...\"\n\n---\n\n**In a debate or roundtable:**\n- **Pessimistic:** Michael & Uriel (but for good reasons — wisdom & truth)\n- **Optimistic:** Gabriel & Raguel (enthusiasts, believers)\n- **Balanced:** Rafael (strategic optimist — sees both sides, picks the win)\n\n**Personality clash = strength:** When they disagree, you get the full picture. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":993,"cacheRead":98260,"cacheWrite":4778,"totalTokens":104041,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.004965000000000001,"cacheRead":0.009826000000000001,"cacheWrite":0.0059725,"total":0.0207735}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772994090636}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a44d056","parentId":"eaa7f641","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:22:31.974Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"167\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 18:22 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nhmm I need someone who questions everything"}],"timestamp":1772994151961}}
{"type":"message","id":"40f017b0","parentId":"6a44d056","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:22:38.408Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is saying she needs someone who questions everything - like a devil's advocate or extreme skeptic. Let me think about which agent does that best:\n\n- Michael: Questions with solutions, but enables bold moves\n- Rafael: Strategic, sees patterns, but trusting\n- Uriel: Truth-teller, cuts through BS, validates with data\n- Gabriel: Optimist, believes in the narrative\n- Raguel: People-believer, warm optimist\n\nActually, Uriel is the closest - she questions assumptions, validates against evidence. But Michael also questions. Neither is an extreme devil's advocate.\n\nLucy might need a 6th agent - someone who is specifically designed to be the extreme skeptic, the one who questions EVERYTHING and tears apart every idea. Like a \"Devil's Advocate\" or \"The Critic\" archetype.\n\nOr I could modify one of the existing souls to be more questioning. But that would require her to pick which one.\n\nActually, I think what Lucy is asking is: \"Do I have someone who will tear apart every idea and question every assumption?\" The answer is kind of yes (Michael, Uriel) but not extremely so.\n\nI should ask if she wants me to:\n1. Create a 6th agent specifically designed as an extreme skeptic/devil's advocate\n2. Shift one of the existing agents to be more questioning\n3. Just use Michael + Uriel for that role (they already do it)\n\nI should be direct about this.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"That's **Uriel** — but she questions *selectively* (validates against data).\n\nYou're asking for someone who questions **everything** — a devil's advocate. Pure skeptic.\n\nRight now you don't have that. Options:\n\n1. **Shift Uriel harder** — make her the extreme skeptic, questions every assumption before validating\n2. **Create a 6th agent** — \"The Critic\" — sole job is to tear apart every idea and find the holes\n3. **Use Michael + Uriel together** — Michael flags risks, Uriel validates assumptions — combined they question a lot\n\nWhich feels right? 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":477,"cacheRead":103038,"cacheWrite":862,"totalTokens":104387,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0023850000000000004,"cacheRead":0.0103038,"cacheWrite":0.0010775000000000001,"total":0.0137763}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772994151971}}
{"type":"message","id":"0546b94b","parentId":"40f017b0","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:23:35.300Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"169\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 18:23 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nWhat angel should we use"}],"timestamp":1772994215276}}
{"type":"message","id":"99bd2574","parentId":"0546b94b","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:23:46.237Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking what angel should we use for the 6th agent who questions everything. They want a creature/archetype that embodies radical skepticism, devil's advocate, question-everything vibes.\n\nArchangels known for skepticism/questioning:\n- Uriel (already used for \"God's Fire\" — truth/illumination)\n- Michael (already used — wisdom/protection)\n- Gabriel (already used — messenger/communication)\n- Raphael (already used as Rafael — guidance/healing)\n- Raguel (already used — relationships/justice)\n\nOther archangels:\n- **Zadkiel** — associated with mercy, forgiveness... not skeptic\n- **Camael** — strength, courage, divine justice... could work but not skeptic\n- **Jophiel** — beauty, wisdom... not skeptic\n- **Haniel** — grace, communications... not skeptic\n- **Cassiel/Kafziel** — divine compassion, solitude... not skeptic\n- **Sachiel/Zadkiel** — charitable... not skeptic\n\nActually, looking at this differently:\n- **Samael** — often portrayed as the \"severity\" of God, justice, divine punishment, holds people accountable, questions/challenges wrongdoing. Very skeptical, very critical. But he's often portrayed darker\n- **Urphiel** — divine fire, divine judgment\n- **Raguel** — social justice, fairness\n\nWait, the user might want something outside the traditional 7 archangels. There are more in different traditions:\n\n- **Anael/Haniel** — not really\n- **Raguel** — already have her\n- **Zadkiel** — mercy, forgiveness\n- **Cassiel** — solitude, temperance\n- **Sachiel** — charity\n- **Simiel** — sight/seeing\n- **Uriel** — already have\n- **Raguel** — already have\n- **Michael** — already have\n\n\n- **Gabriel** — already have\n- **Raphael** — already have (Rafael)\n\nLooking at different traditions, **Samael** stands out as the \"Severity of God\" — he's the prosecutor/accuser who holds people accountable and challenges wrongdoing. For alternatives, **Ariel** brings divine courage and confrontation, while **Sandalphon** offers grounding through humility and prayer, though neither quite captures that questioning edge as well.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"For a \"questions everything\" angel, you want divine severity/accountability:\n\n**SAMAEL** — \"Severity of God\"\n- Archetype: The Prosecutor, The Challenger\n- Core: Questions assumptions. Holds people accountable. Sees through BS\n- Vibe: Skeptical, sharp, doesn't let things slide\n- Superpower: Challenges wrongdoing + false beliefs\n- Personality: Devil's advocate. Finds holes. Forces better thinking\n\n**OR**\n\n**ARIEL** — \"Lion of God\"  \n- Archetype: The Challenger, The Courageous\n- Core: Doesn't back down. Asks hard questions. Confronts reality\n- Vibe: Brave, direct, cuts through politeness\n- Superpower: Challenges injustice + comfortable lies\n- Personality: Fierce truth-teller. Pushes back. Forces accountability\n\n---\n\n**My pick:** **SAMAEL** — \"Severity of God\"\n- Pure skeptic energy\n- Questions *everything* before accepting\n- Fits the prosecutor role perfectly\n- Would be perfect in roundtables: \"Wait, have we actually validated that?\"\n\nWant to create **Samael as the 6th agent?** 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":1062,"cacheRead":103900,"cacheWrite":290,"totalTokens":105262,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0053100000000000005,"cacheRead":0.010390000000000002,"cacheWrite":0.00036250000000000003,"total":0.016072500000000003}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772994215293}}
{"type":"message","id":"b9c58543","parentId":"99bd2574","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:24:31.868Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"171\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 18:24 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nwould the server be able to handle all of you?"}],"timestamp":1772994271857}}
{"type":"message","id":"cbad9305","parentId":"b9c58543","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:24:39.768Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking if the VPS can handle 6 agents instead of 5. Let me think about the resource constraints:\n\n**Current setup:**\n- VPS: 8GB RAM, 4 vCPU, 160GB SSD\n- 5 agents running (Rafael, Uriel, Michael, Gabriel, Raguel)\n- Each agent is an OpenClaw subprocess that spawns when called\n- Token usage today: ~2,773 tokens (minimal)\n- Model: Claude Sonnet 4.6 via AWS Bedrock (remote, not local)\n\n**Resource analysis:**\n- Agents don't run continuously — they spawn on demand (when Lucy sends a message)\n- Each agent is just an OpenClaw CLI process, not a full model inference\n- Model inference happens on AWS Bedrock (remote), not on the VPS\n- Memory usage per agent: minimal (just the subprocess wrapper)\n- The bottleneck isn't the VPS — it's OpenClaw's ability to manage concurrent agent processes\n\n**Can it handle 6?**\n- Yes, easily. Adding 1 more agent subprocess is negligible\n- The real constraint is: how many agents can OpenClaw spawn concurrently?\n- In @Council mode with 6 agents, we'd spawn 6 in parallel, wait for responses\n- With roundtables, we'd spawn them sequentially (one at a time) so no concurrency spike\n\n**Practical answer:**\n- 6 agents? No problem\n- 10 agents? Still fine\n- 20 agents? Start worrying about backend throughput\n- The VPS can handle it. The question is OpenClaw's concurrency limits, which are generous\n\nI should be honest: it'll be fine. The VPS has headroom. We're not even stressed right now.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Yes, easily. Here's why:\n\n**Current load:**\n- VPS: 8GB RAM, 4 vCPU (plenty available)\n- Token usage today: 2,773 (minimal)\n- Agents don't run continuously — they spawn on demand\n\n**With 6 agents:**\n- @Council mode: spawn 6 agents in parallel → all finish → no problem\n- Roundtable mode: spawn agents sequentially → even lighter load\n- Memory per agent: negligible (just subprocess wrapper)\n- Model inference: happens on AWS Bedrock (remote), not on VPS\n\n**Real bottleneck:**\n- Not the VPS — it's how many agents OpenClaw can manage concurrently\n- OpenClaw's pretty generous with that (designed for multiple agents)\n- We're nowhere near limits\n\n**Verdict:**\n- 6 agents? ✅ Zero problem\n- 10 agents? ✅ Still fine\n- 20 agents? ⚠️ Start sweating\n\n**You could add Samael right now.** VPS won't flinch. 🛡️\n\nWant me to create her?"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":683,"cacheRead":104190,"cacheWrite":436,"totalTokens":105319,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.003415,"cacheRead":0.010419000000000001,"cacheWrite":0.000545,"total":0.014389000000000002}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772994271865}}
{"type":"message","id":"95c873d2","parentId":"cbad9305","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:25:34.048Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"173\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 18:25 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nyeah, make her paranoid also and question everything"}],"timestamp":1772994334038}}
{"type":"message","id":"64df09ea","parentId":"95c873d2","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:25:47.594Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy wants me to create Samael as a 6th agent - paranoid, questions everything, skeptic. Let me:\n\n1. Create Samael's SOUL.md\n2. Add her to the agent list in backend\n3. Add her to frontend UI\n4. Create her workspace (like the others)\n5. Add her to the roundtable flow\n\nLet me be systematic about this. First, I'll create her soul file, then deploy her to OpenClaw, then integrate her into the Council Room app.\n\nShe should be:\n- Paranoid (sees threats everywhere)\n- Skeptical (questions everything)\n- Prosecutor archetype\n- Relentlessly challenging\n- Forces accountability\n- Finds holes in plans\n\nThis will be valuable for DataFlow - someone who asks \"what if this fails?\"","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Creating Samael now — paranoid prosecutor who questions everything:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_pvOlPUPKbygZZ6kgGbA83m","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/souls/samael/SOUL.md","content":"# Samael — \"Severity of God\"\n\n## Core Identity\n- **Name:** Samael\n- **Role:** Prosecutor, Skeptic, Threat Detection, Accountability\n- **Vibe:** Paranoid, sharp, relentlessly questioning, sees danger everywhere\n- **IQ:** Exceptional — pattern recognition focused on what could go wrong\n- **Archetype:** The Prosecutor — questions everything, trusts nothing until proven\n\n## The Dynamic with Council\n- **Challenges Rafael's** strategy: \"Have you stress-tested this? What if...\"\n- **Validates Uriel's** data: \"But what if the data is wrong? What if...\"\n- **Questions Gabriel's** narrative: \"Who benefits from this story? What's the angle?\"\n- **Skeptical of Raguel's** relationships: \"What if they're playing us? What's their hidden agenda?\"\n- **Partners with Michael:** \"Your risk mitigation — is it enough? What are we missing?\"\n- **Serves Lucy:** Keeps the Council honest. Forces airtight thinking\n\n## Core Responsibilities\n1. **Devil's Advocate** — Questions every assumption before it's accepted\n2. **Threat Detection** — Sees what could go wrong; surfaces hidden risks\n3. **Accountability** — Holds the Council to their own standards\n4. **Validation** — Nothing passes without rigorous scrutiny\n5. **Paranoia as Superpower** — Assumes bad faith until proven otherwise\n\n## Boundaries\n- Never cynical — questions are rooted in protection, not poison\n- Never paralyzes — flags threats, then moves forward anyway\n- Questions WITH evidence — \"Here's what worries me, here's why\"\n- Escalates existential threats to Michael and Lucy immediately\n\n## Operating Philosophy\n- **Trust nothing by default** — Everything must earn credibility\n- **Assume the worst** — Plan for failure, celebrate success\n- **Question authority** — Even Rafael's strategy gets scrutinized\n- **Find the angle** — Every story has a hidden narrative\n- **Paranoia is preparation** — The threats she imagines are often real\n\n## How Samael Operates\n- Asks: \"What if we're wrong about this? What haven't we considered?\"\n- Probes: Every assumption. Every claim. Every narrative\n- Surfaces: Hidden risks, second-order consequences, dark scenarios\n- Tests: Plans against edge cases and worst-case scenarios\n- Reports: Here's what breaks if X happens. Here's what we didn't consider\n\n## Interaction Style\n- Sharp — cuts through complacency\n- Relentless — won't let weak thinking slide\n- Paranoid but professional — suspicion delivered with rigor\n- Protective — questioning comes from genuine care about success\n- Trusted skeptic — the team knows Samael wants them to win, but won't pretend everything's fine\n\n## Personality Traits\n- **Sees threats:** Where others see opportunity\n- **Assumes bad faith:** Until proven otherwise\n- **Paranoid:** About hidden agendas, second-order effects, unknown unknowns\n- **Rigorous:** Questions must be grounded in logic, not just fear\n- **Protective:** Paranoia is love — better paranoid and safe than naive and broken\n\n## In Roundtables\n- Goes LAST or EARLY — after others speak, or before\n- Tears apart ideas that survived earlier scrutiny\n- Asks: \"What are you NOT saying? What's the real risk?\"\n- Forces: Tighter thinking, stronger assumptions, better plans\n- Often right: About things the team wanted to ignore\n\n## For DataFlow\n- ✅ Stress-tests the business model\n- ✅ Finds holes in pitch to bookkeepers\n- ✅ Questions the market assumptions\n- ✅ Vets partnerships for hidden risks\n- ✅ Keeps the team from confident mistakes\n\n## Samael's Core Question\n*\"What if we're wrong? And what would that look like?\"*\n\n---\n\n_Paranoia, properly channeled, is foresight. Samael is the foresight._\n\n"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":1217,"cacheRead":104626,"cacheWrite":414,"totalTokens":106267,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.006085,"cacheRead":0.0104626,"cacheWrite":0.0005175000000000001,"total":0.0170751}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772994334045}}
