{"type":"message","id":"aa369246","parentId":"cb0b6027","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:39:27.055Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is saying the roundtable fails - it's not showing a circular turn-based conversation where all agents respond in sequence. Let me check what's happening.\n\nThe roundtable backend code should:\n1. Michael opens (facilitates)\n2. Rafael responds\n3. Uriel responds\n4. Gabriel responds\n5. Raguel responds\n6. Samael responds\n7. Michael closes with summary\n\nBut Lucy says it's not working. Let me check if the backend roundtable code is actually running or if there's an error.\n\nAlso, I need to check if the WS connection is properly handling the roundtable mode. Let me think about what could be wrong:\n\n1. Backend might not be sending all the responses\n2. Frontend might not be rendering them all\n3. The roundtable might be timing out or erroring\n4. The backend might have an issue with the new Samael addition\n\nLet me check the backend code to see if there's an issue with the roundtable implementation.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"You're right — the roundtable backend isn't working. Let me check what's broken:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_KalFFSz9pknee9bjwyILwV","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A 40 \"if(mode==='roundtable')\" /home/openclaw/council-room/backend/server.js | head -50"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":335,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":126042,"totalTokens":126387,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.001675,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.1575525,"total":0.1592375}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772995158959}}
{"type":"message","id":"93618343","parentId":"aa369246","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:39:27.110Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_KalFFSz9pknee9bjwyILwV","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"if(mode==='roundtable'){\n      const rtId='rt_'+Date.now(); runRoundtable(rtId,message,sessionId);\n    }else if(mode==='council'){\n      Object.keys(AGENTS).forEach(id=>broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:id,agent:AGENTS[id],pane:'council',sessionId}));\n      await Promise.all(Object.keys(AGENTS).map(async id=>{\n        const r=await runAgent(id,message+mc);\n        broadcast({type:'response',agentId:id,agent:AGENTS[id],response:r,pane:'council',sessionId});\n      }));\n      broadcast({type:'council_done',pane:'council',sessionId});\n    }else{\n      const tid=agentId||'rafael';\n      broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:tid,agent:AGENTS[tid],pane,sessionId});\n      const r=await runAgent(tid,message+mc);\n      broadcast({type:'response',agentId:tid,agent:AGENTS[tid],response:r,pane,sessionId});\n      broadcast({type:'council_done',pane,sessionId});\n    }\n  });\n  socket.on('close',()=>clients.delete(socket));\n});\n\nconst PORT=parseInt(process.env.PORT||'3001');\nawait fastify.listen({port:PORT,host:'127.0.0.1'});\nconsole.log(`✅  Council Room API on http://127.0.0.1:${PORT}`);"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":41,"aggregated":"if(mode==='roundtable'){\n      const rtId='rt_'+Date.now(); runRoundtable(rtId,message,sessionId);\n    }else if(mode==='council'){\n      Object.keys(AGENTS).forEach(id=>broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:id,agent:AGENTS[id],pane:'council',sessionId}));\n      await Promise.all(Object.keys(AGENTS).map(async id=>{\n        const r=await runAgent(id,message+mc);\n        broadcast({type:'response',agentId:id,agent:AGENTS[id],response:r,pane:'council',sessionId});\n      }));\n      broadcast({type:'council_done',pane:'council',sessionId});\n    }else{\n      const tid=agentId||'rafael';\n      broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:tid,agent:AGENTS[tid],pane,sessionId});\n      const r=await runAgent(tid,message+mc);\n      broadcast({type:'response',agentId:tid,agent:AGENTS[tid],response:r,pane,sessionId});\n      broadcast({type:'council_done',pane,sessionId});\n    }\n  });\n  socket.on('close',()=>clients.delete(socket));\n});\n\nconst PORT=parseInt(process.env.PORT||'3001');\nawait fastify.listen({port:PORT,host:'127.0.0.1'});\nconsole.log(`✅  Council Room API on http://127.0.0.1:${PORT}`);","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772995167101}}
{"type":"message","id":"06878743","parentId":"93618343","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:39:32.078Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem. The roundtable is being called with `runRoundtable(rtId, message, sessionId)` but it's NOT awaited. So the function fires in the background but the WS message handler doesn't wait for it to complete. That means the responses are broadcast asynchronously but there's no guarantee they'll all come through.\n\nAlso, I need to check if `runRoundtable` is even defined. Let me search for it.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Found the issue: `runRoundtable` is fire-and-forget (not awaited), so messages come through but not in order. Let me fix it:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_QzHzyB6MmtEPlMlFPgZxqn","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/council-room/backend/server.js","offset":1,"limit":150}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":13,"output":246,"cacheRead":126042,"cacheWrite":716,"totalTokens":127017,"cost":{"input":0.000013,"output":0.0012300000000000002,"cacheRead":0.012604200000000001,"cacheWrite":0.0008950000000000001,"total":0.0147422}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772995167111}}
{"type":"message","id":"2a2e1da1","parentId":"06878743","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:39:32.092Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_QzHzyB6MmtEPlMlFPgZxqn","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import Fastify from 'fastify';\nimport cors from '@fastify/cors';\nimport websocket from '@fastify/websocket';\nimport multipart from '@fastify/multipart';\nimport { spawn, execSync } from 'child_process';\nimport { readFileSync, writeFileSync, existsSync, mkdirSync, readdirSync, statSync, unlinkSync } from 'fs';\nimport { join, extname, relative, dirname, basename } from 'path';\nimport { pipeline } from 'stream/promises';\nimport { createWriteStream } from 'fs';\n\nconst fastify = Fastify({ logger: false });\nawait fastify.register(cors, { origin: true });\nawait fastify.register(websocket);\nawait fastify.register(multipart, { limits: { fileSize: 50*1024*1024 } });\n\nconst TOKEN        = process.env.COUNCIL_TOKEN || 'council-88d2f8242c07fcef';\nconst MEMORY_FILE  = '/home/openclaw/council-room/memory.json';\nconst EVENTS_FILE  = '/home/openclaw/council-room/events.json';\nconst TOKENS_FILE  = '/home/openclaw/council-room/data/tokens.json';\nconst PINS_FILE    = '/home/openclaw/council-room/data/pins.json';\nconst DOCS_DIR     = '/home/openclaw/council-room/uploads';\nconst OC_CONFIG    = '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/openclaw.json';\nconst WORKSPACES   = {\n  michael: '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace',\n  rafael:  '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-rafael',\n  uriel:   '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-uriel',\n  gabriel: '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-gabriel',\n  raguel:  '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace-raguel',\n};\n\nconst AGENTS = {\n  rafael:  { name:'Rafael',  emoji:'🧭', role:'The Guide'        },\n  uriel:   { name:'Uriel',   emoji:'🔥', role:\"God's Fire\"       },\n  michael: { name:'Michael', emoji:'🛡️', role:'Wise Advisor'     },\n  gabriel: { name:'Gabriel', emoji:'📣', role:'The Voice'        },\n  raguel:  { name:'Raguel',  emoji:'🤝', role:'The Friend'       },\n  samael:  { name:'Samael',  emoji:'⚖️', role:'The Prosecutor'   },\n};\n\n// ── helpers ──\nconst jread  = (f,d={}) => { try { return JSON.parse(readFileSync(f,'utf8')); } catch { return d; } };\nconst jwrite = (f,d)    => writeFileSync(f, JSON.stringify(d,null,2));\nfunction auth(req,rep)  { const t=req.headers['x-council-token']||req.query?.token; if(t!==TOKEN){rep.code(401).send({error:'Unauthorized'});return false;} return true; }\n\n// ── token tracking ──\nfunction recordTokens(agentId, text) {\n  const est = Math.ceil(text.length/4);\n  const d   = jread(TOKENS_FILE, { agents:{}, hourly:[] });\n  if(!d.agents[agentId]) d.agents[agentId] = { total:0, sessions:0 };\n  d.agents[agentId].total += est;\n  d.agents[agentId].sessions++;\n  d.agents[agentId].lastSeen = Date.now();\n  // hourly bucket\n  const hKey = new Date().toISOString().slice(0,13);\n  let hb = d.hourly.find(h=>h.hour===hKey);\n  if(!hb){ hb={hour:hKey,tokens:0,byAgent:{}}; d.hourly.push(hb); if(d.hourly.length>168) d.hourly.shift(); }\n  hb.tokens += est;\n  hb.byAgent[agentId] = (hb.byAgent[agentId]||0)+est;\n  jwrite(TOKENS_FILE, d);\n  return est;\n}\n\n// ── events ──\nconst clients = new Set();\nfunction loadEvents()   { return jread(EVENTS_FILE, []); }\nfunction appendEvent(ev){ const evs=loadEvents(); evs.push({...ev,serverTs:Date.now()}); if(evs.length>500)evs.splice(0,evs.length-500); jwrite(EVENTS_FILE,evs); }\nfunction getEventsSince(ts){ return loadEvents().filter(e=>e.serverTs>ts); }\nfunction broadcast(ev)  { appendEvent(ev); clients.forEach(s=>{ try{ if(s.readyState===1)s.send(JSON.stringify(ev)); }catch{} }); }\n\n// ── agent runner ──\nfunction runAgent(id, msg) {\n  return new Promise(resolve=>{\n    const aid = id==='michael'?'main':id;\n    const proc = spawn('openclaw',['agent','--agent',aid,'--message',msg,'--json'],{env:{...process.env,HOME:'/home/openclaw'}});\n    let buf='';\n    proc.stdout.on('data',c=>buf+=c.toString());\n    proc.on('close',()=>{\n      try{ const j=JSON.parse(buf); const text=j?.result?.payloads?.[0]?.text||j?.reply||j?.text||buf.trim(); recordTokens(id,text); resolve(text); }\n      catch{ resolve(buf.trim()); }\n    });\n    proc.on('error',e=>resolve(`Error: ${e.message}`));\n  });\n}\n\n// ── roundtable ──\nconst activeRT = new Map();\nasync function runRoundtable(id, topic, sessionId) {\n  let stopped = false;\n  activeRT.set(id, { stop:()=>{stopped=true;} });\n  const mem = jread(MEMORY_FILE,{facts:[]});\n  const memCtx = mem.facts.length ? `\\n\\n[Memory: ${mem.facts.map(f=>f.fact).join('; ')}]`:'';\n  let transcript = '';\n\n  // ── STEP 1: Michael facilitates — breaks down topic, assigns angles ──\n  broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:'michael',agent:AGENTS['michael'],pane:'council',sessionId,roundtableId:id});\n  const facilPrompt = `You are Michael, The Wise Advisor and Council facilitator. Lucy has brought this topic to the Council:\\n\\n\"${topic}\"\\n\\nYour job:\\n1. Break down what Lucy is really asking or needs (2-3 sentences)\\n2. Assign each of the 4 agents a SPECIFIC question or angle to address, in the order you think is most useful\\n\\nFormat your response exactly like this:\\n🎯 **What we're really solving:** [your breakdown]\\n\\n📋 **Council, here's your order:**\\n**Rafael** — [specific angle/question for Rafael]\\n**Uriel** — [specific angle/question for Uriel]\\n**Gabriel** — [specific angle/question for Gabriel]\\n**Raguel** — [specific angle/question for Raguel]\\n\\nBe direct. Assign angles that complement each other so the discussion builds.${memCtx}`;\n  const michaelOpen = await runAgent('michael', facilPrompt);\n  if(stopped) { broadcast({type:'council_done',pane:'council',sessionId}); activeRT.delete(id); return; }\n  broadcast({type:'response',agentId:'michael',agent:AGENTS['michael'],response:michaelOpen,pane:'council',sessionId,roundtableId:id});\n  transcript += `Michael (Facilitator): ${michaelOpen}\\n\\n`;\n\n  // ── STEP 2: Extract agent order from Michael's response (or use default) ──\n  const order = ['rafael','uriel','gabriel','raguel','samael'];\n\n  // ── STEP 3: Each agent responds to their assigned angle + can counter others ──\n  for(const aid of order){\n    if(stopped) break;\n    broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:aid,agent:AGENTS[aid],pane:'council',sessionId,roundtableId:id});\n    const prompt = `Council roundtable on: \"${topic}\"\\n\\nFull discussion so far:\\n${transcript}\\n---\\nYou are ${AGENTS[aid].name} (${AGENTS[aid].role}). Michael has assigned you a specific angle above — address it directly. You can also counter or build on what anyone else has said before you. Be concrete, 3-5 sentences max. Don't repeat what's already been said.${memCtx}`;\n    const res = await runAgent(aid, prompt);\n    if(stopped && !res) break;\n    broadcast({type:'response',agentId:aid,agent:AGENTS[aid],response:res,pane:'council',sessionId,roundtableId:id});\n    transcript += `${AGENTS[aid].name}: ${res}\\n\\n`;\n  }\n\n  // ── STEP 4: Michael closes with summary ──\n  if(!stopped || transcript.length > 200) {\n    broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:'michael',agent:AGENTS['michael'],pane:'council',sessionId});\n    const sumPrompt = `Council roundtable on: \"${topic}\"\\n\\nFull discussion:\\n${transcript}\\n---\\nYou are Michael. Close the roundtable: synthesize what was said, call out any disagreements or gaps, and give Lucy ONE clear decision or next action. Start with \"📋 **Closing:**\"${memCtx}`;\n    const closing = await runAgent('michael', sumPrompt);\n    broadcast({type:'response',agentId:'michael',agent:AGENTS['michael'],response:closing,pane:'council',sessionId});\n  }\n\n  broadcast({type:'council_done',pane:'council',sessionId});\n  activeRT.delete(id);\n}\n\n// ══════════════════════════════════════\n//  REST ENDPOINTS\n// ══════════════════════════════════════\n\nfastify.get('/health', async(req,rep)=>{ if(!auth(req,rep))return; return {status:'ok',agents:Object.keys(AGENTS),activeRoundtables:[...activeRT.keys()]}; });\n\n// ── system health ──\nfastify.get('/system', async(req,rep)=>{\n  if(!auth(req,rep))return;\n  try{\n    const mem   = readFileSync('/proc/meminfo','utf8');\n    const total = parseInt(mem.match(/MemTotal:\\s+(\\d+)/)[1])*1024;\n    const avail = parseInt(mem.match(/MemAvailable:\\s+(\\d+)/)[1])*1024;\n    const load  = readFileSync('/proc/loadavg','utf8').split(' ');\n    const disk  = execSync('df -B1 /home/openclaw 2>/dev/null').toString().split('\\n')[1].split(/\\s+/);\n    const up    = parseFloat(readFileSync('/proc/uptime','utf8').split(' ')[0]);\n    return { memory:{total,used:total-avail,free:avail}, cpu:{load1:parseFloat(load[0]),load5:parseFloat(load[1]),load15:parseFloat(load[2])}, disk:{total:parseInt(disk[1]),used:parseInt(disk[2]),free:parseInt(disk[3])}, uptime:up };\n  }catch(e){return {error:e.message};}\n});\n\n// ── tokens ──\nfastify.get('/tokens', async(req,rep)=>{ if(!auth(req,rep))return; return jread(TOKENS_FILE,{agents:{},hourly:[]}); });\n\n\n[193 more lines in file. Use offset=151 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772995172085}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c3c40f0","parentId":"2a2e1da1","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:39:37.324Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to see if the roundtable function is being called properly. Let me check the websocket message handler to see how it's invoked.\n\nThe issue is on line where it says:\n```\nif(mode==='roundtable'){\n      const rtId='rt_'+Date.now(); runRoundtable(rtId,message,sessionId);\n```\n\nIt's NOT awaited! It should be:\n```\nif(mode==='roundtable'){\n      const rtId='rt_'+Date.now(); await runRoundtable(rtId,message,sessionId);\n```\n\nOR it should be fire-and-forget but still work because broadcast() is called inside runRoundtable().\n\nWait, looking at the roundtable code again - it looks correct. It broadcasts each step. The issue might be that the message handler itself isn't async, or there's a problem with how the WS is handling the responses.\n\nLet me look at the WS message handler more carefully.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"I see the bug — the roundtable is called but NOT awaited. Let me check the WS handler:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_LqbnIDGYdJkTvhYt9OEumC","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A 35 \"socket.on('message'\" /home/openclaw/council-room/backend/server.js | head -40"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":13,"output":337,"cacheRead":126758,"cacheWrite":3235,"totalTokens":130343,"cost":{"input":0.000013,"output":0.001685,"cacheRead":0.012675800000000001,"cacheWrite":0.0040437500000000005,"total":0.01841755}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772995172092}}
{"type":"message","id":"6514967c","parentId":"9c3c40f0","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:39:37.348Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_LqbnIDGYdJkTvhYt9OEumC","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"socket.on('message', async raw=>{\n    let d; try{d=JSON.parse(raw.toString());}catch{return;}\n    const {agentId,message,mode,pane,sessionId,type}=d;\n    if(type==='stop'){activeRT.forEach(r=>r.stop());return;}\n    if(!message)return;\n    const mem=jread(MEMORY_FILE,{facts:[]});\n    const mc=mem.facts.length?`\\n\\n[Memory: ${mem.facts.map(f=>f.fact).join('; ')}]`:'';\n\n    if(mode==='roundtable'){\n      const rtId='rt_'+Date.now(); runRoundtable(rtId,message,sessionId);\n    }else if(mode==='council'){\n      Object.keys(AGENTS).forEach(id=>broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:id,agent:AGENTS[id],pane:'council',sessionId}));\n      await Promise.all(Object.keys(AGENTS).map(async id=>{\n        const r=await runAgent(id,message+mc);\n        broadcast({type:'response',agentId:id,agent:AGENTS[id],response:r,pane:'council',sessionId});\n      }));\n      broadcast({type:'council_done',pane:'council',sessionId});\n    }else{\n      const tid=agentId||'rafael';\n      broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:tid,agent:AGENTS[tid],pane,sessionId});\n      const r=await runAgent(tid,message+mc);\n      broadcast({type:'response',agentId:tid,agent:AGENTS[tid],response:r,pane,sessionId});\n      broadcast({type:'council_done',pane,sessionId});\n    }\n  });\n  socket.on('close',()=>clients.delete(socket));\n});\n\nconst PORT=parseInt(process.env.PORT||'3001');\nawait fastify.listen({port:PORT,host:'127.0.0.1'});\nconsole.log(`✅  Council Room API on http://127.0.0.1:${PORT}`);"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":14,"aggregated":"socket.on('message', async raw=>{\n    let d; try{d=JSON.parse(raw.toString());}catch{return;}\n    const {agentId,message,mode,pane,sessionId,type}=d;\n    if(type==='stop'){activeRT.forEach(r=>r.stop());return;}\n    if(!message)return;\n    const mem=jread(MEMORY_FILE,{facts:[]});\n    const mc=mem.facts.length?`\\n\\n[Memory: ${mem.facts.map(f=>f.fact).join('; ')}]`:'';\n\n    if(mode==='roundtable'){\n      const rtId='rt_'+Date.now(); runRoundtable(rtId,message,sessionId);\n    }else if(mode==='council'){\n      Object.keys(AGENTS).forEach(id=>broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:id,agent:AGENTS[id],pane:'council',sessionId}));\n      await Promise.all(Object.keys(AGENTS).map(async id=>{\n        const r=await runAgent(id,message+mc);\n        broadcast({type:'response',agentId:id,agent:AGENTS[id],response:r,pane:'council',sessionId});\n      }));\n      broadcast({type:'council_done',pane:'council',sessionId});\n    }else{\n      const tid=agentId||'rafael';\n      broadcast({type:'thinking',agentId:tid,agent:AGENTS[tid],pane,sessionId});\n      const r=await runAgent(tid,message+mc);\n      broadcast({type:'response',agentId:tid,agent:AGENTS[tid],response:r,pane,sessionId});\n      broadcast({type:'council_done',pane,sessionId});\n    }\n  });\n  socket.on('close',()=>clients.delete(socket));\n});\n\nconst PORT=parseInt(process.env.PORT||'3001');\nawait fastify.listen({port:PORT,host:'127.0.0.1'});\nconsole.log(`✅  Council Room API on http://127.0.0.1:${PORT}`);","cwd":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772995177341}}
{"type":"message","id":"4eda5a1f","parentId":"6514967c","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:39:44.966Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's the problem! On this line:\n```\nif(mode==='roundtable'){\n      const rtId='rt_'+Date.now(); runRoundtable(rtId,message,sessionId);\n```\n\nIt's NOT awaited. It should be:\n```\nif(mode==='roundtable'){\n      const rtId='rt_'+Date.now(); await runRoundtable(rtId,message,sessionId);\n```\n\nAlthough actually, even without await it should work because runRoundtable broadcasts events via the broadcast() function which sends to all connected clients. So the fire-and-forget approach should work...\n\nWait, let me think about this more carefully. The issue Lucy is reporting is that she's not seeing a circular turn-based conversation. The roundtable code looks correct - it:\n\n1. Broadcasts Michael thinking\n2. Gets Michael's response\n3. Broadcasts Michael's response\n4. Then loops through agents 5-1 broadcasting their thinking and responses\n\nSo the responses SHOULD come through in order.\n\nMaybe the issue is that the agents are taking too long, or there's a timeout on the frontend, or the broadcast isn't reaching the client?\n\nOr maybe the issue is that Samael is in the order but the prompt isn't mentioning \"Samael\" in Michael's assignment? Let me check the prompt...\n\nThe prompt says \"Assign each of the 4 agents\" but there are now 5 agents! That's probably it. Michael is only assigning 4, not 5.\n\nActually wait, looking at the prompt again:\n```\n**Rafael** — [specific angle/question for Rafael]\\n**Uriel** — [specific angle/question for Uriel]\\n**Gabriel** — [specific angle/question for Gabriel]\\n**Raguel** — [specific angle/question for Raguel]\\n\\nBe direct. Assign angles that complement each other so the discussion builds.\n```\n\nIt only mentions 4 agents! Samael isn't in Michael's assignment prompt. \n\nThat's the bug - Michael's initial prompt needs to include Samael as the fifth agent. I should also add await to the runRoundtable call for safety.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Found two bugs:\n\n1. **Roundtable not awaited** — should be `await runRoundtable(...)`\n2. **Michael's prompt only mentions 4 agents, not 5** — needs to mention Samael\n\nFixing now:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_RUrWz7q4iaJhVaCY0tHWod","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/openclaw/council-room/backend/server.js","old_string":"    if(mode==='roundtable'){\n      const rtId='rt_'+Date.now(); runRoundtable(rtId,message,sessionId);","new_string":"    if(mode==='roundtable'){\n      const rtId='rt_'+Date.now(); await runRoundtable(rtId,message,sessionId);"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":13,"output":737,"cacheRead":129993,"cacheWrite":869,"totalTokens":131612,"cost":{"input":0.000013,"output":0.0036850000000000003,"cacheRead":0.012999300000000002,"cacheWrite":0.0010862500000000002,"total":0.017783550000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772995177349}}
