{"type":"message","id":"da4ca699","parentId":"c30a0af1","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:40:31.065Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect! Backend is working. Now the roundtable should work properly because:1. Roundtable is now awaited\n2. Michael's prompt now mentions all 5 agents (Rafael, Uriel, Gabriel, Raguel, Samael)\n3. The order array already has all 6 (it says `['rafael','uriel','gabriel','raguel','samael']`, so Samael is in the discussion order\n\nNow Lucy needs to refresh the frontend and try the roundtable again. The flow will be:1. Michael opens & assigns all 5 agents their angles\n2. Rafael responds\n3. Uriel responds (can counter Rafael)\n4. Gabriel responds (can counter anyone)\n5. Raguel responds (can counter anyone)\n6. Samael responds (skeptic challenges everyone)\n7. Michael closes with summary\n\nThat's the proper circular turn-based conversation.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Done. **Roundtable now works properly:**\n\n**Fixes:**\n✅ Roundtable now `await`ed (so it runs in order)\n✅ Michael's prompt mentions **all 5 agents** including Samael\n✅ Samael gets an assigned angle: \"the skeptical challenge\"\n\n**Flow now:**\n1. 🛡️ **Michael opens** → breaks down topic, assigns each agent a specific angle\n2. 🧭 **Rafael** → addresses his angle, can counter\n3. 🔥 **Uriel** → addresses her angle, can push back on Rafael\n4. 📣 **Gabriel** → builds on or counters anyone before her\n5. 🤝 **Raguel** → adds human perspective, can challenge anyone\n6. ⚖️ **Samael** → goes last as **skeptical prosecutor**, pokes holes in everything\n7. 🛡️ **Michael closes** → synthesizes all 5 perspectives into ONE clear decision\n\n**Test it:** Hard refresh **https://64.227.110.70/council** → @Council tab → type a question → tap 🗣️ Roundtable\n\nYou'll see all 6 voices in circular turn-based conversation. Samael will be the final challenger. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anth