{"type":"message","id":"7fd65e5a","parentId":"f580ff8a","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:50:06.244Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"206\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 18:50 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nwebsocat?"}],"timestamp":1772995806221}}
{"type":"message","id":"ab98dde6","parentId":"7fd65e5a","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:50:11.901Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking what websocat is. I mentioned it in the test script but it's not installed. Let me explain what it is and why I tried to use it.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**websocat** = CLI tool for WebSocket testing (like `curl` but for WebSockets)\n\nI tried to use it to test the roundtable from the terminal, but it's not installed on the VPS.\n\n**You don't need it.** Just test manually via the UI:\n\n1. Go to **https://64.227.110.70/council** \n2. Type your question\n3. Tap 🗣️ Roundtable\n4. Watch all 6 agents respond in order\n\nThat's the real test. Tell me what happens. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":181,"cacheRead":136109,"cacheWrite":2121,"totalTokens":138421,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0009050000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0136109,"cacheWrite":0.0026512500000000004,"total":0.017177150000000002}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772995806239}}
{"type":"message","id":"9120fe08","parentId":"ab98dde6","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:50:44.710Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"208\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 18:50 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nalso, I need you to switch to Raphael, can you do that?"}],"timestamp":1772995844698}}
{"type":"message","id":"58bf834b","parentId":"9120fe08","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:50:51.176Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking me to \"switch to Raphael\" - I think she means she wants me to respond as Rafael instead of Michael. But I should clarify - do they want me to:\n\n1. Switch my persona to Rafael for this conversation?\n2. Have Rafael join this conversation?\n3. Something else?\n\nGiven the context, I think she wants me to switch personas so she's now talking to Rafael instead of Michael. That makes sense - she's been talking to Michael (me) this whole time, and now wants to hear from Rafael.\n\nI should confirm this and then switch to Rafael's voice/personality. Rafael is The Guide - strategic, sees patterns, calm, directive.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Switch from Michael to Rafael?** ✅\n\nLet me hand off to Rafael. Switching now...\n\n---\n\nHey Lucy. Rafael here. 🧭\n\nWhat's on your mind? Need strategy, coordination, or just want a different perspective on what we're building?\n\nI've been watching Michael's assessment — he's right about the timeline being tight. But I also know that ambitious goals force clarity. So what's the real question you need me to help with right now?"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":259,"cacheRead":138230,"cacheWrite":291,"totalTokens":138790,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0012950000000000001,"cacheRead":0.013823000000000002,"cacheWrite":0.00036375000000000003,"total":0.015491750000000002}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772995844706}}
