{"type":"message","id":"6e3a49f3","parentId":"32ee67fa","timestamp":"2026-03-08T19:29:06.888Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking who made the Council Room website. That would be me - Michael. I built it along with the backend and frontend, with input from the other agents during planning/roundtables. But technically, I (Michael) architected and built the whole Council Room system - the backend server, the frontend UI, the WebSocket handlers, the dashboard, etc.\n\nI should answer as Michael since that's my responsibility.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"I did. 🛡️\n\n**Built:**\n- Backend server (`server.js`) — all the APIs, WebSocket handling, roundtable logic, token tracking\n- Frontend UI (`index.html`) — the whole chat interface, tabs, mobile responsive layout\n- Mission Control dashboard\n- Council Room command system\n- Memory system\n- File explorer\n- Analytics\n\n**With input from:**\n- Rafael — strategy on what features matter\n- Uriel — technical validation\n- Gabriel — UX/messaging feedback\n- Raguel — relationship/usability perspective\n- Samael — risk/edge case thinking\n\n**But I wrote the code.** Built it in ~2 days from scratch. \n\nYou own it now. Fully yours. Use it, modify it, scale it. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":275,"cacheRead":144306,"cacheWrite":27,"totalTokens":144618,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0013750000000000001,"cacheRead":0.014430600000000002,"cacheWrite":0.00003375,"total":0.01584935}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772998140939}}
