{"type":"message","id":"75be7cc8","parentId":"f02154f9","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:19:47.023Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OH. I see what Lucy is saying.\n\nOn the Council Room website, there's a LABEL that says \"Rafael\" but the person responding is actually Michael (me).\n\nAnd then on Telegram, there's ANOTHER agent claiming to be Michael, but they're actually Rafael.\n\nSo the agents are MIXED UP or SWAPPED in some way.\n\nLucy is saying:\n- The one labeled \"Rafael\" on the website is actually me (Michael), and I sent Lemon\n- The real Michael (me on Telegram) sent Avocado\n- But that doesn't make sense because I'm the same person\n\nWait... let me re-read.\n\n\"Raphael said she's Michael\" - Rafael claimed to be Michael? Or Rafael said Michael's signature is Lemon?\n\nActually I think what's happening is:\n\nOn the website, there are 6 chat panes. One is labeled \"Rafael\" but when Rafael responds in that pane, she's not actually Rafael - she's Michael pretending to be Rafael? Or the labels are wrong?\n\nOr worse: the agents are actually swapped somehow. The agent labeled \"Rafael\" is actually running as Michael's agent, and vice versa.\n\nThis would be a serious infrastructure problem - agent IDs don't match labels.\n\nLucy is pointing out: \"You think you're Michael on Telegram, but the one labeled Rafael on the website is also you (Michael).\"\n\nSo either:\n1. I'm logged in as both Michael AND Rafael (credential confusion)\n2. The agent routing is wrong (Rafael's agent ID is pointing to Michael's code)\n3. The frontend labels are wrong (showing Rafael when it's actually Michael responding)\n\nThis is a BIG BUG.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**OH. I see the problem now.** 🛡️\n\nThe agent labels are **SWAPPED or CONFUSED.**\n\nOn the Council Room website:\n- The pane labeled \"🧭 Rafael\" is actually running as me (Michael) → I sent Lemon\n- But I THINK I'm Michael on Telegram → I sent Avocado\n\nSo either:\n\n1. **Agent routing is broken** — Rafael's agent ID is pointing to Michael's workspace/model\n2. **Frontend labels are wrong** — showing \"Rafael\" when it's actually Michael responding  \n3. **Credential confusion** — I'm logged in as both agents somehow\n\n**This is a critical bug.** The agents are mixed up.\n\nLet me check the agent bindings:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_PMKIEZxwwzk6X9ShQXV4jo","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw agents list 2>&1 | grep -E \"id|workspace|Agent\""}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":10,"output":624,"cacheRead":151907,"cacheWrite":332,"totalTokens":152873,"cost":{"input":0.000009999999999999999,"output":0.0031200000000000004,"cacheRead":0.015190700000000001,"cacheWrite":0.00041500000000000006,"total":0.0187357}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773022778685}}
