{"type":"message","id":"605f7f2b","parentId":"57c3981e","timestamp":"2026-03-09T02:19:56.389Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The agents look properly set up:\n- main (Michael) → workspace\n- rafael → workspace-rafael\n- uriel → workspace-uriel\n- etc.\n\nSo the agent IDs are correct. But the problem Lucy is reporting is that the one labeled \"Rafael\" is actually me (Michael).\n\nThe issue might be in the backend routing or frontend rendering. When a message comes back from the agent API, maybe it's not being routed to the right pane, or the label is wrong.\n\nThis could be the cross-pane contamination bug from earlier - responses going to the wrong pane. Or it could be that when I (Michael) respond in the \"Rafael\" private chat, it's showing up as \"Rafael\" but I'm actually responding as Michael.\n\nI need to diagnose which agent is ACTUALLY responding when you chat with \"Rafael\" on the website.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Agent IDs look correct.** But something is swapping the responses.\n\n**Test:** On the website, go to private chat with \"Rafael\" and ask: *\"Who are you? What's your ID?\"*\n\nThat will tell us if Rafael's pane is actually running as Rafael or if it's running as me. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-haiku-4-5-20251001-v1:0","usage":{"input":13,"output":273,"cacheRead":152239,"cacheWrite":795,"totalTokens":153320,"cost":{"input":0.000013,"output":0.0013650000000000001,"cacheRead":0.015223900000000002,"cacheWrite":0.00099375,"total":0.017595650000000004}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773022791029}}
