{"type":"message","id":"6bb2c9b5","parentId":"cf975d1b","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:31:15.708Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_SZCvVrECQumaTUvQqOCD63","toolName":"session_status","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.2 (85377a2)\n🕒 Time: Monday, March 9th, 2026 — 7:31 AM (UTC)\n🧠 Model: amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1 · 🔑 unknown\n🧮 Tokens: 5 in / 365 out\n🗄️ Cache: 100% hit · 530k cached, 492 new\n📚 Context: 177k/200k (89%) · 🧹 Compactions: 1\n🧵 Session: agent:main:main • updated just now\n⚙️ Runtime: direct · Think: off · elevated\n🪢 Queue: collect (depth 0)"}],"details":{"ok":true,"sessionKey":"agent:main:main","changedModel":false,"statusText":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.2 (85377a2)\n🕒 Time: Monday, March 9th, 2026 — 7:31 AM (UTC)\n🧠 Model: amazon-bedrock/us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1 · 🔑 unknown\n🧮 Tokens: 5 in / 365 out\n🗄️ Cache: 100% hit · 530k cached, 492 new\n📚 Context: 177k/200k (89%) · 🧹 Compactions: 1\n🧵 Session: agent:main:main • updated just now\n⚙️ Runtime: direct · Think: off · elevated\n🪢 Queue: collect (depth 0)"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773041475698}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc80d7ea","parentId":"6bb2c9b5","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:31:24.576Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yeah — **177k out of 200k (89% full).** 🔴\n\nI'm close to the limit. When I hit 200k, I'll start losing older context (compaction kicks in — already happened once).\n\n**What this means:**\n- I might forget earlier parts of our conversation\n- Complex tasks get harder (less room to think)\n- Responses may get shorter/less detailed\n\n**Options:**\n1. **Start a new session** — fresh 200k context, but I lose this conversation\n2. **Keep going** — I'll compact again, losing older details but keeping recent context\n3. **Save critical context to memory files first** — then start fresh\n\n**My recommendation:** Let me save everything important to memory files right now, then you can start a fresh session when needed. The memory files survive across sessions. 🛡️"}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":191,"cacheRead":176040,"cacheWrite":321,"totalTokens":176553,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.004775000000000001,"cacheRead":0.08802,"cacheWrite":0.0020062500000000002,"total":0.09480625000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773041475708}}
{"type":"message","id":"c645e0cc","parentId":"cc80d7ea","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:31:57.551Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"468\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"sender\": \"ICat\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-09 07:31 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ICat (1058350976)\",\n  \"id\": \"1058350976\",\n  \"name\": \"ICat\",\n  \"username\": \"icattj\"\n}\n```\n\nhow can i increase from 200k to 400k?"}],"timestamp":1773041517534}}
{"type":"message","id":"c1c4d6bc","parentId":"c645e0cc","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:32:15.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy is asking how to increase the context window from 200k to 400k. This is a model/provider limitation, not something I can change easily.\n\nClaude Opus 4.6 has a 200k token context window - that's the model's maximum. To get more context, you'd need:\n\n1. A model with a larger context window\n2. Or use techniques like RAG, summarization, etc.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The 200k limit might be configurable in OpenClaw settings, or it might be the model's hard limit.\n\nClaude models:\n- Claude 3.5 Sonnet: 200k context\n- Claude 3 Opus: 200k context\n\n\n- Claude 4 Opus: likely 200k context as well\n\nThe context window is determined by the model itself, not by OpenClaw configuration. Since Claude Opus maxes out at 200k, Lucy would need to either switch to a different model that supports larger contexts like Gemini with up to 1M tokens, or implement workarounds like better memory management or retrieval-augmented generation.\n\nI could also suggest starting fresh sessions more frequently with well-organized memory files to keep things manageable.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Short answer:** You can't — it's a model limit, not an OpenClaw setting.\n\n**Claude Opus 4.6 = 200k max.** That's the ceiling. No config change fixes it.\n\n**Ways to get more context:**\n\n| Option | Context | Cost |\n|--------|---------|------|\n| Stay on Claude Opus 4.6 | 200k | Current |\n| Switch to **Gemini 2.5 Pro** | **1M tokens** | Need Google API key |\n| Switch to **GPT-4o** | 128k (less) | Need OpenAI key |\n| Switch to **Claude Sonnet** | 200k (same, cheaper) | Already available |\n\n**Best option for 400k+:** **Gemini 2.5 Pro** — 1 million token context window. 5x what we have now.\n\n**Or smarter approach:** Don't chase bigger context. Instead:\n- Save everything to memory files (survives forever)\n- Start fresh sessions (full 200k each time)\n- Memory files = unlimited context across sessions\n\n**My honest take:** 200k is enough if we use memory files properly. The real fix isn't more tokens — it's better memory management. Which I should be doing anyway. 🛡️\n\nWant me to set up Gemini, or focus on better memory? "}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":679,"cacheRead":174619,"cacheWrite":2023,"totalTokens":177324,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.016975,"cacheRead":0.0873095,"cacheWrite":0.01264375,"total":0.11694325}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773041517544}}
