{"type":"message","id":"cfb4bf14","parentId":"c72ae3bc","timestamp":"2026-03-09T07:33:14.270Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lucy wants all agents to reset - meaning start fresh sessions. Let me save the current memory state first, then explain how to reset.\n\nActually, \"reset\" in OpenClaw context means starting fresh conversations. The agents don't have persistent running sessions - they respond on-demand. So there's nothing to \"reset\" per se.\n\nBut what Lucy probably means is: clear the context/conversation history so everyone starts fresh. This would mean:\n1. Save important context to memory files\n2. Clear session history\n\nLet me first save everything important to memory, then reset.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Let me save everything to memory first, then reset all sessions:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_MIru5sTFrWcCOIRwZm63zA","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Update daily memory file with latest context\ncat >> /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-08.md << 'EOF'\n\n## Late Night Session (March 8-9, 2026)\n\n### What was built/fixed:\n- Council Room v2: full rebuild with 5 tabs (Chat, Mission Control, Analytics, Files, Settings)\n- 40+ features implemented (all tabs, command palette, theme toggle, etc.)\n- Samael (6th agent) deployed — The Prosecutor, questions everything\n- File upload in chat (images + documents, drag & drop, paste support)\n- Real agent health monitoring (pings each agent, shows latency)\n- Roundtable fixed: Michael opens → Rafael → Uriel → Gabriel → Raguel → Samael → Michael closes\n- Rafael got own Telegram bot (8513953061:AAFMeFzePJqggMNhDFX83D7KK7cJG0zxFq8)\n- File-editor skill created to avoid edit mistakes\n- Memory synced across all 6 agent workspaces\n\n### Known bugs:\n- Rafael may be displaying Michael's shield icon on Council Room\n- Agent health check endpoint is slow (~10s per agent)\n- Model shown as Opus